title: baked ham polish(szynka pieczona)
directions: Score ham.
Place pineapple rings and cherries on ham with toothpicks.
Put in pan and pour ginger ale over it.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, basting every 1/2 hour with juice in pan.
Remove from oven and make paste out of mustard, brown sugar and pan juice to get spreading consistency.
Spread on ham.
Raise temperature to 425° for 15 minutes.

title: almond mushroom sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add mushrooms and onion; saute.
Add flour; blend well.
Add salt, pepper and chicken stock; cook until smooth and thick.
Add lemon juice and almonds.
Serve over baked chicken loaf.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towels to remove moisture. Press hash browns onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate to form a crust.
Sprinkle on salt and some dry onion.
Drizzle melted butter over crust.
Bake in 425° oven for 25 minutes. Remove from oven; reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Toss together the ham and cheese.
Place in crust.
Beat milk with the eggs and seasoning salt.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
tags: loose pack frozen hash brown potatoes

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease cookie sheet. Combine cake mix, oats and sugar. Combine oil and eggs; add to dry ingredients. Mix well. Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy strawberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water, eggs and food coloring.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove to cool on rack.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into greased oblong pan.
Sprinkle a few more chocolate chips on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut when cooled.
My favorite! Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cappuccino(dessert coffee)
directions: Mix in a large	20
cup coffee pot.
Mix some hot black coffee to
dissolve
Nestle Quik, then add milk and remaining coffee. Heat
to
boiling point (do not boil), then add creme de cacao and
brandy.
Serve hot in glass mugs or coffee cups with whipped cream.
Reddi-Wip cream may be used.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool completely. Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar, vanilla and cream cheese well, then pour over completely cooled crust.
Mix milk with pudding mix. Pour over second layer.
Top with balance of Cool Whip.
Top over Cool Whip with nuts or grated Hershey candy bar.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: pork with snow peas
directions: Place pork in a dish.
In a small bowl, mix together soy sauce, bean paste, 1 tablespoon peanut oil and Rose wine or sherry.
Then pour over pork.
Turn slices to coat.
Marinate 1 hour.
Drain and reserve marinade.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on jelly roll pan.
Cream the cream cheese, oleo, dill weed and onion.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crust.
Sprinkle with any combination of fresh vegetables (cut small).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° then cool.
Cut in squares. Serve.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot muffins
directions: In bowl, mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Using a whisk, add the remaining ingredients one at a time.
Fill greased muffin tins 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until blended. Spread into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: crawfish etoufee
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers in margarine. Add remaining ingredients.
Add cayenne pepper and seasoning to taste. Simmer.
Serve over white rice.

title: mother's jam cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter, then add 2 eggs and buttermilk.
Add flour, soda and baking powder, then mix.
Add raisins, nuts, coconut, blackberry jam and vanilla.
Bake in 3 layers in round cake pans that have been greased with shortening and sifted with flour.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: roast beef sandwiches
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, mustard and pepper; spread on buns. Layer each sandwich with lettuce, tomato, pepper, onion, roast beef and Bleu cheese; add top halves of buns.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender, not brown.
In a large mixing bowl, add rest of ingredients to noodles, onion and celery.
Withhold 1 cup of grated cheese.
Season with Accent, celery salt and pepper.
Toss lightly until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into buttered Pyrex dish; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cover with foil for first half of cooking.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oils and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Mix into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix with hands.
Form into large ball or smaller ones.
Seal in wax paper and refrigerate.
Can freeze up to 6 months.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, and cooking oil; beat well. Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, and salt; add gradually to egg mixture; mix well. Add persimmons and mix well. Pour into 1 large or 2 small pans. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Drain fruit cocktail,
Mix all ingredients, except crusts, together in bowl.
Blend well.
Put into crust and chill 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: jackpot
directions: Brown beef with onion; add soup, water and noodles.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add beans, one-half of cheese and seasonings. Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese veggie soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 quart of water.
Add celery, carrots, potatoes and onions.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add broccoli and cauliflower and cook 15 minutes more.
Add soup and cheese; heat and serve.

title: coconut impossible pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 9-inch buttered pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Forms own crust.

title: choco-chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars well; add eggs and beat well.
Add soda to creamed mixture.
The vanilla adds well here also.
Mix in the dry ingredients and stir well.
Drop on well-greased cookie sheet and cook at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: cool lime pie
directions: Heat 7-Up to boiling and pour over Jell-O in a bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add ice cream; stir.
Chill until partially set. Pour into crust and chill.
Stir occasionally as it sets.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Line bottom
of
a
x
2-inch pan with graham cracker
crumbs.
Slice
bananas and place over crumbs.
Slice ice cream and place over banana layer; sprinkle 1/2 cups nuts. Freeze until firm.
Combine sugar, milk and chocolate chips in a
medium saucepan;
cook
over low heat until thick.
Remove from
heat; add
vanilla.
Cool
completely.
Pour
chocolate mixture over ice cream layer;
spread Cool Whip over top, then sprinkle
with remaining
nuts.
Freeze
until
serving time. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.	Yield: 9 to 12 servings.

title: low-fat pink salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and jello.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, onion and hamburg; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: almond-glazed orange chiffon cake
directions: Bake our orange chiffon cake mix as directed.
Cool.
Combine 1/3 cup heated milk, corn syrup, almond extract and creamy white frosting mix.
Beat until smooth.
If too thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons more milk.
Pour slowly over cake.
Sprinkle top with chopped, toasted almonds.
Glaze will set within 1/2 hour.
Store any leftover glaze in refrigerator.

title: carob crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet, shaping together. Cook about 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet with spatula, pushing together while warm.
They will be crisp when cool.

title: kahlua ice cream cake
directions: Ladyfinger cookies, with or without cream.
If with cream, divide in half.
Line bottom and sides of tube pan with ladyfingers.
Layer chocolate ice cream and crushed Heath bars. Pour Kahlua over candy.
Layer Heath bar ice cream on top. Freeze.
tags: Ben and Jerry's chocolate ice cream

title: the real old fashion italian cookies
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Shape dough into "S's" or make small braids.
Bake at 350° until brown for about 8 minutes. Add glazed icing.
Mix confectioners sugar, water and flavoring of almond or anise to paste consistency.
Put on tops.
Can add sprinkles (optional).

title: yummy amaretto fruit dip
directions: Mix all together with mixer and use for dipping fresh fruits. Store any leftovers (if you have any) in fridge.
Always a hit.

title: eggplant oyster casserole
directions: Cube eggplant and cook in water with a little onion juice. Drain well.
Butter casserole dish.
Layer cracker crumbs, eggplant and dots of butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour oyster stew over and top with more cracker crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: bill's baked beans
directions: Wash and sort beans; simmer, covered, in water for 30 minutes. Drain; reserve stock.
Combine remaining ingredients and Cowboy bacon or salt pork cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole; add beans.
Cover with stock.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 7 to 8 hours.
Stir occasionally; add liquid as needed.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, buttermilk, soda, salt and melted margarine or shortening.
Add bran flakes and mix thoroughly. This makes a large amount to be kept in the refrigerator 6 to 8 weeks.
Use as needed.
You may add pecans, walnuts or coconut or put jelly in the middle before taking out of the oven or anything you might like, something new each morning.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to
25 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Leave in pie plate.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add salt and put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish in layers with noodles and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla. Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add egg, blend well. combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix until blended. Drop by teaspoonful, 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten slightly with a fork. Bake at 375 degrees for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend the cream cheese with the 2 tablespoons melted margarine until smooth. Add the chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion or chives.
Mix well.
Separate the rolls into 4 rectangles.
Seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center of mixture; seal. Brush top with 1 tablespoons melted margarine. Dip in seasoned croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: johanna's aebleskiver
directions: Mix by hand.
Add dash of vanilla.
Beat 4 egg whites stiff. Fold into batter.
Use oil to fry.

title: pumpkin-oatmeal bites
directions: Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter until softened.
Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Beat in pumpkin.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats and raisins or chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven about 12 minutes or until done.
Remove from sheet and cool. Makes about 120 cookies.

title: breakfast pie(quiche)
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into 2 frozen pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a rapid boil with salt.
Gradually stir in grits with a fork.
Cook until all water is absorbed.
Stir in butter bit by bit.
Carefully add eggs, cheese, garlic and cayenne pepper.
Put into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk and meat. Put in ungreased baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk; pour evenly over the first ingredients.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli casserole #11
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli.
Place broccoli in a baking dish and pour mixture over.	Top with 6 to 8 crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: spinach-mushroom salad
directions: In salad bowl, combine spinach and mushrooms.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over spinach mixture and toss gently to combine.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Cut bread into cubes, set aside.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs.
Next add pineapple.
Blend with spoon, then fold onto bread cubes.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Delicious served as side dish with ham.

title: granny's lasagne
directions: Brown meat with seasonings.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes; cook for 2 hours on low heat.
While meat is on low heat, let cream cheese soften, then add milk to a pouring consistency.
Cook noodles according to box instructions.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine, add sugars and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans, pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey divan
directions: In a flat Pyrex dish, put a layer of broccoli and turkey (or chicken).
Prepare sauce by mixing remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over broccoli and turkey; top with bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This can be made ahead and heated.
Can also be frozen.

title: italian-style zucchini-pasta
directions: Cook pasta.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook onion, carrot and garlic in hot oil for 5 minutes, or until tender.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, fennel seed and crushed red pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir in pasta; heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grinath sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients with milk.
Chill.
Roll and cut into favorite shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until bubbly. Serve with taco chips.

title: paella
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Put the white wine and saffron threads in a small bowl and set aside.
Preheat a large, heavy paella pan or frying pan for about 1 minute over medium-high heat. Spray it 4 times with the vegetable oil.
Saute the onion for 2 to 3 minutes until limp.
Add the rice and saute for about 1 minute until golden.
Add the wine and saffron and stir until the liquid is completely absorbed.
Stir in the peppers.
Add the hot chicken stock 1/4 cup at a time, stirring until absorbed.
Keep the stock over low heat.
When only 1/2 cup of the chicken stock remains to be added, stir in the chicken.
With the last addition of stock, stir in the squid and shrimp.
Turn the burner off.
The rice should be tender.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine cornbread mix, egg and milk; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and crumble; set aside.
Combine tomatoes, green pepper, onion, pickles and bacon.
Toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice; stir well and set aside.
Layer half each of cornbread, tomato mixture and mayonnaise mixture in a large glass bowl.
Repeat layers. Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange creamsicle cake
directions: Bake the cake as directed at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool cake well.
Poke holes in cake with fork (large tines).

Mix together the boiling water, cold water and orange jello; pour over cake slowly so that liquid goes into fork holes (use small spoon). Mix the pudding, milk and Cool Whip together; add flavorings. Spread this mixture over cake.

title: rice casserole
directions: Rinse raw rice several times to get rid of starch.
In skillet, saute rice, butter, onion and celery for 10 minutes.
Put sauteed ingredients in a large bowl.
Add chestnuts, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, soup, water and Kitchen Bouquet.
Pour into greased pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until rice is done.

title: joann's zucchini quiche
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and margarine until tender.
Add basil, oregano, garlic powder and parsley flakes to zucchini mixture. Mix together Mozzarella cheese and eggs.
Spread rolls into pie plate.
Spread mustard over crust.
Add zucchini mixture, then pour cheese and egg mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Blend all ingredients for a cool shake.
You can use frozen strawberries or bananas or not.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel onions, slice thinly (about 5 cups).
Put butter in a 4-quart saucepan; heat over moderately high heat until butter melts.
Add onions and pepper to butter.
Saute onion mixture, stirring often
until onions are a light golden brown.
Sprinkle onions with flour; stir until all traces of flour disappear.
Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Gradually add beef broth, stirring onion mixture all the time; stir in water and bay leaf.
Return to moderately high heat. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low. Cook onion soup, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Discard bay leaf; add salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and sift
flour,
cinnamon,
nutmeg, cloves, baking soda, baking powder and
salt.
Mix sugar and eggs thoroughly. Add oil and mix well
again.
Add
vanilla, zucchini and nuts. Bake in 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef and onion roast
directions: Place the chuck roast in the center of extra wide, heavy-duty foil in a roasting pan.
Brush meat with A.1.
sauce and sprinkle the onion soup mix over it.
Spread mushroom soup over top and sides of meat.
Wrap loosely in the foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 people.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers and put in large mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
This salad is good if put in a covered plastic container and chilled for a couple of hours before serving. Keep well chilled for several days.

title: beef stew dinner
directions: Wash stew meat and place in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Slice vegetables on top of meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Seal with aluminum foil.
Cook in 350° oven for 4 to 5 hours.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Superb on chicken, beef, pork, shrimp or lamb.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Wash zucchini, trim ends, slice and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Cook sausage and onions together. Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese (save some for topping).
Mix eggs, thyme, rosemary, garlic salt, salt, pepper and Accent.
Add crumbs, cheese, eggs and seasonings to sausage, onion and zucchini.
Pour in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order and mix well.
Pour in 2 pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pan-fried fish
directions: Sprinkle
fish	with
salt and pepper.	Blend water and egg. Dip
fish
into
egg, and then coat with Bisquick.	Cook fish in oil for 10 minutes, turning to brown evenly.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cook all ingredients, except nuts, over medium heat, stirring constantly, until apples are tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in nuts.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and suet a little at a time; drain excess fat in colander. Put drained meat into large kettle. Add rest of ingredients. Cook slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Mix Casa Marina and water. Makes a paste. Add to meat mixture and simmer 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook and drain manicotti shells.
Brown meat and garlic (drain off fat).
Blend cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese, also salt and mayonnaise, in a large bowl.
Fill each shell with filling. Place in single layer in baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining filling (if any) between shells.
Cover with Ragu sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sterling fruit dip
directions: In blender mix fruit cocktail, cream cheese and pudding mix until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip to taste.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: cream of wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms until crisp. Stir in flour.
Slowly add broth. Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in wild rice and half and half.
Blend in salt and pepper.
Continue cooking over low to medium heat for 1 hour.

title: white fruit cake(for those who hate fruitcakes.)
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except fruit and nuts.
Cream butter and sugar. Combine with the dry ingredients. Add fruit and nuts. Mix. Fold in egg whites. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 275° and 1 hour at 300°.

title: mrs. tom harvey's date meringues(cornerstone cookery)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Flour nuts and dates to keep them from sticking together.
Mix all.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the dry ingredients in a bowl. Blend all other ingredients in a blender and add to dry ingredients.
Stir just to mix.
Line muffin pan with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake for 16 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven; mix well. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat to simmer.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients, then put through sieve.
Add salt. Then add remaining ingredients.
After all the ingredients are done, cook and put in jars.
Cold pack 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with Pam. Cook spaghetti twists according to package directions and drain.

title: chicken fajita potato
directions: Scrub potatoes, prick skins and microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: henry mack's hot rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into bowl.
Add sugar, salt and water.
Add 1/2 of the flour and beat well.
Beat in eggs, shortening and remaining flour.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Place into greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with clean towel and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down dough and turn out onto lightly floured board.
Form dough into smooth balls and place on greased round or square cake pans.
Let rise in warm place until doubled (about 45 minutes).
Bake at 350° to 375° about 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, brush lightly with melted margarine.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese and onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish with tomato slices. Makes 6 servings.

title: meringue shell
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until stiff and dry.
Add sugar and continue beating until sugar has dissolved.
On an oiled baking sheet, spoon mixture into a 9-inch round.
With spoon, push sides up around circle like center is shelled out so sides are at least 1-inch high.
Bake at 275° until almost tinted.
Turn off heat and leave in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Fill with prepared lemon, chocolate or butterscotch pie filling.

title: party pizzas
directions: Place pepperoni slice on cracker.
Add 1 teaspoon pizza sauce. Top with cheese.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese is slightly browned and bubbly (or may microwave approximately 45 seconds, watch closely if microwaving, as cheese melts quickly).
Serve immediately.
May secure with toothpicks, if desired.

title: artichoke hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook onion in water; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spread in greased 7 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Peel and chop the peaches.
Mix well with sugar and lemon juice.
Stir in cream.
Add enough whole milk to fill 1 gallon freezer container.
Delicious and easy!

title: pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven cook bacon till crisp. Drain off all but 2 tbsp drippings from pan. Crumble bacon and set aside. Sprinkle all sides of meat with lemon pepper. Brown meat in reserved drippings.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat together margarine, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mustard potatoes
directions: Peel and slice thin.
Mix other ingredients together.
Put 1/2 of potatoes in bottom of pan.
Pour half mix on top.
Add other half of potatoes and the balance of mixture.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 400°.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Butter 9x13 inch pan.
Microwave 5 cups of marshmallows, chocolate chips, corn syrup and butter on high 2-3 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal.
Quickly toss until evenly coated. Stir in remaining marshmallows.
Press mixture into pan.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Cut and enjoy.

title: sweet and sour vegetables
directions: Combine sugar, dry mustard, salt, vinegar, oil, onion and poppy seed.
Pour over raw broccoli, carrots, green pepper and zucchini.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: soul food
directions: In a heavy skillet chop bacon and fry until done, but not crisp. Remove from skillet and set aside. Leave 3-4 Tbsp. of bacon drippings in skillet and add green pepper and onion. Cook until onion is clear, then cut cabbage into small pieces and add to skillet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook about 10 minutes. Continuing to stir. Add bacon pieces and cover with lid, simmer about 20 minutes. Add 1 c. tomatoes and heat
through.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat oil, butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add 5 egg yolks, vanilla and milk.
Sift soda and flour together; add.
Then add coconut and nuts.
Beat whites stiff and gently fold into batter. Bake at 350°.
Pour into 3 cake pans.

title: hominy salad
directions: Cook hominy; drain and let cool.
Add egg, then desired amounts of tomato, onion, bell pepper and mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and green pepper until tender.
Add meat and brown until crumbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Remove cover and bake 15 minutes.

title: tasty tots
directions: Cut bacon strip in half. Wrap around Tater Tot. Add a toothpick to hold. Bake at 400° until bacon is done. Good for parties and sleepovers. Serve with pizza sauce.

title: 5 bean salad
directions: Drain beans. Add celery, onions and green pepper in bowl. Mix vinegar, sugar and salad oil; pour over beans. Refrigerate.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put beans in casserole dish.
Place fried onion rings on top of beans.
Top with mushroom soup.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and let stand until thick. Add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Cook together juice, sugar, egg, butter and flour.
When thickens, remove from heat.
Chill.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over Jell-O.
Sprinkle cheese over salad.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Simmer ingredients (except fruit slices) together in saucepan for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Serve hot with orange or lemon slices and a cinnamon stick garnish.
Serves 4.

title: oriental rice-texas style
directions: In a large pot, cook rice and chicken noodle soup mix with the water.
Have lid on until rice is done. Set aside.
Brown sausage lightly chopping it into small pieces.
Lift out sausage and set aside. Drain off most of the fat and discard. Chop onion, bell pepper and celery into coarse pieces and saute in skillet with remaining fat until barely tender.
I add a touch of water and cover pan to help the cooking. When tender, add the vegetables and sausage to the rice and stir, tossing lightly.
Makes a large recipe, but it reheats well.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Beat well; add spices and fruit.
Bake in layers at 350°.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Stir in eggs and almond extract.
Stir in almonds.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoonful onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 275° until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets immediately. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. (Soften cream cheese slightly in microwave before mixing.) Add salt and vanilla; beat well. Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition. Add sifted flour a little at a time. Beat well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken breasts in phyllo with dijon(yield: 6 servings)
directions: 1. In a large skillet, melt 4 Tbsp. butter, add chicken and cover.
Saut over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Heat oil in saucepot. Add beef and cook until browned. Pour off fat. Add mushroom soup, 1 c. water and soup mix. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat about 1 to

1-1/2 hours. Add potatoes and carrots. Cover and cook 1 hour or until roast is fork-tender. Remove roast and vegetables to platter. Mix flour and remaining water. Add to soup mixture. Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set out a cookie sheet.
Cook in skillet over medium heat ground beef.
Drain grease, spread on cookie sheet over chips.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and oleo for 3 minutes, then add soda and vanilla.
Take off burner.
Pour over popped corn; don't pack in pan.
Heat in oven at 200° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad for diabetics(low-fat)
directions: Drain fruits and save juices; heat juices and use to dissolve Jell-O.
Cool and add Coca-Cola.
Chill until thick.
Stir in cream cheese, fruits and nuts.
Chill again until firm, then cut into serving size pieces.

title: country garden potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until just tender.
Dice and put in shallow casserole dish.
Moisten with milk.
Mix peppers, onions, parsley and cheese and sprinkle over potatoes.
Drizzle with melted butter and season.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: overnight tuna casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except 1/4 cup reserved cheese.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 12 hours or overnight.
Microwave on High for 15 to 17 minutes, until bubbly.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Let stand, uncovered, 5 to 7 minutes, until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Put in ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
While warm, cut in bars.
Cool.
Makes 48 bars.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover chicken with water and bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour or until tender. Remove chicken and let cool.
Bone chicken and chop meat; set aside.
Separate broccoli into spears.
Cook broccoli, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; stir well.
Set aside.
Arrange broccoli in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; top with chicken and soup mixture.
Combine breadcrumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole; return to oven 5 minutes.

title: grilled red snapper
directions: Spray vegetable spray to the center of 4 pieces of foil about twice the size of the fillet.
Put 1/4 of the onions over the sprayed area of each foil.
Add fillet.
Top each fillet with 1/4 of lime slices, the chopped tomato, pepper and thyme.
Seal foil tightly, folding twice.
Grill over hot coals or in oven 7 to 12 minutes or when fish flakes with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Cream butter,
sugar
and
salt until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and
egg
yolks one at a time.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and
mix.
Mix
in poppy seed.
Shape into balls.
Place on lightly
greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Press in center of each
cookie
with thumb.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove
from cookie sheet and cool.
Press in center again.
When cool, fill center with melted chocolate bits.

title: deviled crab
directions: Make into cakes and warm in oven if you like.
Or, mix well and place in ramekins or crab shells.
Place on tray and put under broiler until brown.
(The onion and bell pepper can be sauteed in butter if you like.)

title: frozen peanut butter cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together; add peanut butter, milk and whipped topping.
Pour into pie crust and freeze at least 4 hours.
Remove from freezer at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: french casserole
directions: Fry the bacon in a skillet until it is brown; remove it and set aside.
Drain off the excess fat, leaving enough to brown the meat in.
Cook the beef until it is dark brown.
Place the meat and bacon in a casserole.
Add the next 3 ingredients and enough wine to cover.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Brown the onions and mushrooms in a little bacon grease.
Add them to the meat.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes longer.
Add more wine if needed.
Serve with rice.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Cool and add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and freeze.
Take out 3 hours before serving.
Pour 2 large bottles of ginger ale or 7-Up over mixture.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When cold, add remaining ingredients. Pour into 6-cup mold or in individual molds.
Chill at least 2 hours before unmolding on lettuce.
Serves 10.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain. Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, peppers and tomato sauce. Add a dash of cumin (optional). Mix all together. Pour in a 7 x 13-inch glass baking dish or 2-quart casserole dish.

title: sparkling apple punch
directions: Combine apple cider, papaya nectar and ice in punch bowl. Add papaya and orange slices.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Mix yolks, milk, butter and crackers.
Cook in microwave for 8 to 10 minutes until liquid is gone.
Add beaten egg whites to sugar and spread over the top.
Brown in conventional oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a Bundt or tube pan.
Combine Bisquick, cheese, sugar, dill weed and dry mustard and set aside.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken.
Mix rest of ingredients and place in pan, greased.
Place chicken on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Add Jello and dissolve. Add applesauce and put into refrigerator until firm.

title: imperial strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Use Cool Whip to layer:
Cool Whip on top, mixture, Cool Whip, mixture on bottom.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
When using the frozen vegetables, heat the mixture on the stove until the vegetables are about done (approximately 15 minutes).
Spoon into prepared crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top of crust and brush lightly with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: goodnight-loving trail buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine 3 cupfuls of flour, 1 teaspoonful of baking soda and 2 teaspoonfuls salt, with lard the size of an egg.
Add to this enough buttermilk or clabber to make a soft dough.

Mix thoroughly, then dump onto a well floured board; knead lightly with your fingers until the dough does not stick to your fingers. Use light pressure of hand or rolling pin to about 1/2-inch thick. Cut with cutter, or squeeze with hands into biscuits.
Place in a well-greased pan, using melted lard.
Take a tablespoon and spoon enough lard on each biscuit to cover them well.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) until brown.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Wash rice carefully and place in a large saucepan with water and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until boiling point is reached.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Drain and rinse with cold water. Drain once more.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put in a small casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top .
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Layer fruits in 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour and sprinkle over fruit.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese over top.
Finely crush 1 roll Ritz crackers. Sprinkle over cheese.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ground meat and corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add drained corn, soups, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Add noodles.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion. Add the brown sugar.
Salt and pepper. Add the Worcestershire sauce and the catsup.
Simmer (the longer, the better).

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 1/4 sticks of butter or margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Spread and press in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat on high speed 1 3/4 sticks of butter or margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs until thick and creamy like pudding.
Spread evenly on crumb crust.
Slice bananas and lay on this mixture.
Spread pie filling over bananas.
Drain pineapple well and spread evenly over pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and chopped maraschino cherries on top.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: chocolate-nut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion.
Drain and then add next 4 ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Heat each tortilla in small amount of oil.
Sprinkle small amount of cheese on each and roll up and place in electric skillet.
Pour meat mixture over these. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and heat on low.
These enchiladas can also be put in a 12 x 14-inch pan and heated in oven.
Good with pot of dry pinto beans.

title: devil ham dip
directions: Mix Devil ham and cream cheese.
Add ketchup to desired thickness.
This will thicken in refrigerator.

title: camping cobbler
directions: Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french toast
directions: Break the eggs and put them into a mixing bowl.
Add the milk, vanilla and salt.
Use a fork to mix well.
Put frying pan on stove over low heat.
Put the butter into pan and spread it as it melts. Put a piece of bread into mixture and soak it.
Then put it into the frying pan.
Do this for all pieces of bread.
Cook the pieces until they are brown on one side, then turn over and brown the other side.
Eat right away!
Can put cinnamon and sugar on it or maple syrup or jam.
Yields 2 servings.

title: blender cake
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until well mixed. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
Ice while hot.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry ground beef and onions; drain.
Add enchilada sauce and cream of chicken soup.
Heat in casserole dish.
Crumble chips and layer chips, meat and cheese.
Make 2 layers and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ken's beer battered fish
directions: Mix in a large bowl buttermilk baking mix, onion powder and garlic powder.
Stir in egg yolk and beer until blended.
Beat egg white with mixer until stiff with rubber spatula.
Fold into batter.
Moisten fish with water and dip fish into batter.
Deep fry in hot oil until lightly browned.

title: pea wiggle
directions: Make white sauce by melting shortening in saucepan.
Add flour and milk, stirring all the time.
Bring to a boil.
When mixture is smooth, add peas and tuna.
Serve over potatoes or rice.

title: dutch oven chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in Dutch oven.
Arrange onion slices over chicken.
Combine all remaining ingredients and blend together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy heavenly hash
directions: Melt chips in large bowl. Stir in milk, pecans and marshmallows. Stir until well coated. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper until hard.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Open the clams; drain off and save the juice and remove the clams from the shells.
Chop the clams or put them through a meat grinder.
(See "How To Prepare Clams" under Broiled Stuffed Clams recipe.)

title: reindeer sandwich
directions: Cut bread in half on diagonal.
Spread each half with peanut butter.
Use small, thin pretzels as antlers, raisins for eyes and the red candy for Rudolph's nose.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix melted butter, eggs, and vanilla.
Add white and brown sugar and mix well.
Add flour.
Add other ingredients and pour into a long pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: one-bowl brownie
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in a microwave safe bowl on High for 2 minutes until margarine is melted.
Stir in sugar. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and serve, makes 24.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain well.
Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bread crumbs are golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together well. Store in covered container. Add 1/3 cup of mix to each cup of hot water.

title: spring rhubarb salad
directions: Combine rhubarb, water and sugar.
Cook until rhubarb is tender.
Add to remaining ingredients.

title: buffalo wings sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add hot sauce and vinegar.
Simmer over low heat.

title: chicken amandine
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Use to coat chicken.
In 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon butter, cook chicken breasts until browned and fork-tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cover bottom of an 8 x	12
x 2-inch dish with lettuce. Add salt and pepper.
Layer
remaining	ingredients
in
order given. Cover and allow to	remain in refrigerator for about 8 hours.

title: hobo cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix into stiff dough.
Roll into small balls; put on greased sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with yeast.
Stir water, milk, butter, sugar and salt over low heat until butter melts.
Cool for about 5 minutes.
Add flour and yeast.
Add remaining flour, nuts, fruit and eggs.
Dough will be stiff.
Knead on floured board until the dough is smooth and elastic and the raisins are well distributed. Coat each coffee can with oil.
Divide the dough into two equal pieces and place into the cans.
Cover the cans with plastic tops. Let rise in warm place (85°) until the dough is 1 inch from the top of the cans.
Remove tops.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until the top is golden brown and/or sounds hollow when tapped.

title: lemon chiffon pie(from:  american heart association cookbook)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add grated lemon rind and 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Stir well.
Cool until the mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites (about 20 minutes.)
Place nonfat dry milk and ice water in a mixing bowl.
With an electric mixer, beat on high speed 3 to 4 minutes until soft peaks form. Add lemon juice and continue beating.
Add the remaining 1/4 cup of sugar gradually and continue beating until stiff peaks form. Fold into gelatin mixture and combine thoroughly.
Pour into cooled crust.
Chill until firm (about 3 hours).

title: rum balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Shape into 1 to 1 1/2 inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar, pecans or dry cocoa.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomatoes, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Use 400° oven.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients except paraffin wax and chocolate. Roll into egg shape, then place on buttered cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to coat, melt 1/3 of a block of paraffin to a pound of chocolate.
Roll eggs in chocolate.
Remove. Place on cool rack to dry.

title: shrimp, peas and rice stir-fry
directions: Cook black-eyed peas as directed on package.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet until hot.
Stir-fry carrots and onion for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, garlic, thyme and red pepper; stir-fry vegetables about 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; stir-fry until shrimp are pink about 2 minutes.
Add rice, black-eyed peas and combine with shrimp mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with green onions.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gribee
directions: Mix sugar and butter until creamy, then add flour.
Roll to 3/4
inch thickness, then cut into shape and place 1/2 blanched almond on top.
Bake for 15-20 mins in 300° oven.

title: vanilla sauce(sissy's sauce for mama's bread pudding)
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in water.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients and spoon hot over pudding.

title: mother's muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir together buttermilk, egg, sugar and butter.
Blend, then add dry ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin cups at 400° for 23 minutes.

title: 7 course dinner
directions: Place all ingredients (except tomato soup and water) into a large casserole.
Pour tomato soup and water over top.
Top with a layer of bacon strips.
Bake 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: quick candy
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Stir fast.
Pour in a greased dish.

title: 7-bean bake
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Save grease for celery and onions and fry them.
Drain wax, green, kidney and butter beans.
Add chili and pork and beans.
Mix tomato soup, mustard and brown sugar together.
Pour over beans.
Fry bacon and crumble on top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can French fried onions. Place mixture in a casserole dish. Cook at 350° for 20-30 minutes. Add remaining onion rings to top of casserole and brown.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° in glass dish).

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken breasts and vegetables in 6-quart soup pot.
Add 2 quarts water.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken, slice and return to pot.

title: candy coated peanuts
directions: Put all
ingredients in heavy frying pan and bring to a boil. Cook and stir until sugar melts and then gets dry again and coats peanuts.
Spread peanuts on cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven (300°) and bake 15 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: a faithful mother's recipe for a wonderful family
directions: Sift these together thoroughly and add the appropriate amount of work and play.
Season with trust and faith and place in a pan well-greased with a sense of humanity.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs, pumpkin, and 1 Tbsp. vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Pour into a greased 10 inch tube pan. bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour & 15 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting. Make frosting by beating together cream cheese, margarine, vanilla an powdered sugar. spread on cooled cake.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Put sugar and cocoa together and add milk and butter. Cook 2 minutes on high, then add peanut butter and turn off. Then add oats. Let cool,
then cut into squares.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt; set aside.
Into a large mixing or mixer bowl, sift the flour with the baking powder and soda.
Add the shortening, cut into chunks.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives, a pastry blender or by using your fingers, until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine the liquid ingredients and stir into the flour.
Mix it thoroughly, but do not knead.

Refrigerate, covered, overnight before using or store for up to 1 week in a covered container like a 1 gallon glass jar. Pinch off enough dough to make the desired number of biscuits and return the remainder to the refrigerator.

title: baba maria's best torte
directions: In small bowl, mix breadcrumbs, chopped walnuts and sifted baking powder together.
With mixer, beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and beat well for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites, adding 1 tablespoon sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold in yolks to whites gently.
Fold in dry ingredients, gently.
Do not overblend.
Line 2 (9-inch) round cake pans with waxed paper.
Grease and flour.
Pour batter in pans and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and invert on dish towel.
Peel off wax paper and cool.

title: german skillet supper
directions: In deep skillet, melt margarine, then spread undrained sauerkraut over it.
Sprinkle with rice, then chopped onion.
Top with coarsely crumbled raw ground round and season with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over all and cook, covered, at low heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve from skillet.
Serves 4.

title: peach salad
directions: Place the jello, pineapple and sugar in a small pot.
Heat over low heat until ingredients are dissolved.
Cool and fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: easy spiced cider
directions: Fill coffee percolator with apple cider.
Cover bottom of percolator basket with red hot candies.
Brew until red hots are melted.
Adjust to taste.
Enjoy!

title: ham delights
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; spread on top and bottom of each roll.
Add cheese and ham.
Place in large pan, covered with foil, and bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, until just heated through.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine with spoon and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, eggs and sugar together.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
It will sink in the middle.
A little lemon juice may be added to both layers if desired.

title: snowman cake
directions: Prepare your favorite cake mix.
Grease and flour 2 layer pans, one 8 x 1 1/2-inch and one 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Divide the batter evenly between pans.
Bake as directed on package.
On aluminum foil covered cardboard, place 8-inch layer for head of snowman and 9-inch layer for body.
Frost layers, joining them together. Sprinkle with flaked coconut.
Place large chocolate wafer cookie for earmuffs.
Use semi-sweet chocolate pieces for buttons; gumdrops for eyes, eyebrows and nose.
Use rope licorice for muffler and red shoestring licorice for mouth.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour and milk, alternately, ending with flour. Fold in flavoring by hand.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Start in cold oven.
(Do not open door while baking.)

title: gene's beef stew
directions: Put meat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish; put potatoes, carrots, onion and celery.
Sprinkle tapioca over.
Add tomato juice on top; salt and sugar.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours, covered with foil.

title: confetti rice
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, bring water and soup mix to a boil over medium high heat.
Add margarine and rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Lay chicken flat in a glass baking dish.
Combine a jar of apricot preserves and a small bottle of Catalina dressing.
Pour mixture over chicken; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add water, pumpkin, nuts and raisins.
Add dry ingredients:
flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pans or cans.

title: pralines
directions: Shell enough pecans to make 2 cups pecan meats.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, maple syrup and milk.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boiling point and, without stirring, boil to soft ball stage, 238°.
Remove from heat.
Let stand until cool. Add salt and Mapleine or vanilla.
Beat with wooden spoon or pour onto marble slab and work with spatula until candy begins to harden, then place in saucepan and stir over hot water until softened.
Add nuts.
Drop from spoon in 3-inch rounds onto buttered slab or baking sheet.
Makes about 20 pralines.

title: egyptian celery soup(solomon iv, solomon in his royal cities)
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add onion and cook until limp.
Add celery and toss to cover with butter.
Sprinkle on flour and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add stock and mix thoroughly. Transfer to a saucepan and add remaining stock.
Simmer soup 20 minutes or until celery is tender.
Add cream and season to taste. Serve hot or cold.

title: chili rellenos pie
directions: Split chilies; remove seeds.
Lay flat; rinse and drain.
Rub oil on bottom and sides of two 9 x 13-inch pans or two 9 x 9-inch pans.
Spread 1/2 of the chicken in each pan or pans, skin side down.
Place sliced cheese on chilies; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over cheese and peppers (chilies).
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with salsa.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a casserole dish.
Top with bacon and bake at 350°
until bacon is browned.

title: auntie's green beans
directions: Mix in order given in a 2-quart ovensafe dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake in a 400° oven for two hours or until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Don't skimp on the baking time; the longer it bakes, the better it tastes.

title: florence schwartz amish date pudding
directions: Pour hot water over dates and soda; let stand until cool. Combine all ingredients together and put in pan and bake.
Break into squares and serve with bananas and whipped cream.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix after each addition.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mama's applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Slightly beat eggs; mix with sugar. Sift all the dry ingredients with the exception of soda.
Mix the soda with the applesauce.
Add raisins and nuts with the dry ingredients, then combine all together and beat well.
Bake for 1 hour at 265°.

title: hearty vegetarian chili
directions: In a large kettle, cook onions and green pepper in oil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until onions are golden and pepper is soft.
Add mustard seeds and cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Add chili powder, cumin, cocoa, cinnamon, tomatoes and their liquid, beans and their liquid, carrots, mushrooms, and tomato paste.
Reduce heat and simmer rapidly, uncovered, for about 40 minutes or until most of the liquid has cooked away and chili has thickened; stir frequently to prevent sticking.
*Note: In place of the cooked kidney beans, you may use 3 16-oz. cans of no-salt added kidney beans plus 1 c. water.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in shortening until soft.
Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet, adding 1/2 to 2/3 of the taco seasoning (to taste).
Use fork to break up the meat as it is browning.
Drain hamburger.
Place beans in same skillet the meat was browned in, using a fork to mash the beans to desired consistency.
Mix 1/2 to 2/3 package of taco seasoning in beans while cooking.
Broil to melt cheese.
Layer in 9-inch pie plate or casserole dish sour cream, beans, meat, salsa and cheese.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in saucepan; cook until tender (10 to 12 minutes); drain.
In bowl, mix butter, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables and toss lightly.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together.
Pour over fresh salmon steaks and refrigerate for 6 hours.
Keep turning fish.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes each side or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: really good ring bread
directions: Mix water, yeast, flour, sugar, oil and salt together.
Let rise at room temperature for 1 1/2 hours.
After rising, roll out to 8 x 15 inches.
Spread cheese over bread, spread onion over bread, then sprinkle poppy seed over all.
Roll into a log from long end; form into a jelly roll.
Form into a ring and place on a pizza pan and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: health relish
directions: Mix cucumber, cabbage, pepper and carrots in bowl.
Blend well.
Set aside.
Place mustard seed, celery seed, salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Heat all until warmed, just until sugar dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Pour over vegetables and blend well.
Makes about 6 cups.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread pie crust in pizza pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/2-inch slices.
In a casserole dish, alternate squash, onions, mushroom soup and crumbs.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Seal with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine milk and egg; mix well.
Stir together cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices into egg mixture, then into cornmeal mixture.
Fry tomato slices in hot oil until browned.
Turn once.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Add sugar and blend until creamy. Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Roll puffs while hot in powdered sugar and roll again when cold. Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, using mostly flowerets and upper, more tender parts of stem.
Chop onion.
Add onion, bacon bits, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Blend Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Stir well. Chill 2 hours or more before serving.

title: cascaron
directions: Combine mochiko, coconut and condensed milk.
Add warm water and mix well.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Deep fry until light brown.
Poke 2 to 3 cascarons onto bamboo skewer if you wish. Glaze with melted brown sugar.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Combine fruits and flour.
Mix well.
Pour milk and vanilla over all and mix.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: cheese bars or cheese cake
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan, melt the butter.
Take out and put yellow or chocolate cake mix, plus 1 egg and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Mix this in the pan.
It will be hard to spread.
Mix the powdered sugar, 2 eggs and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
At room temperature mix the cream cheese good and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This will take 1 or 2 hours to cool before you can cut it.

title: white and wild rice medley
directions: Cook and stir almonds, wild rice, mushrooms and green onions in margarine until almonds are golden brown (10 to 15 minutes). Pour wild rice mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in instant bouillon and water.
Cover and cook in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Stir in regular rice.
Cover and cook until liquid is absorbed, about 30 minutes longer.

title: pennsylvania dutch molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Add and beat well the eggs.
Dissolve soda in molasses and add to shortening mixture.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
Add 1/2 to creamed mixture; add 1/2 cup sour or buttermilk with 1 teaspoon of soda dissolved in it to the first mixture.
Then add the rest of the dry ingredients.
Dough will be quite soft.
Chill well.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and bake for 12 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: topping for dutch apple pie
directions: Cut butter into flour; add brown sugar and mix evenly. Sprinkle over top of apples in pie shell, instead of top crust. Enough for 2 pies.

title: festive blitz torte
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place shortening in bowl; add dry ingredients and add milk and vanilla.
Mix until flour is moistened, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 2 eggs and beat 1 minute longer. Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) paper-lined pans.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add 1 cup sugar gradually, beating to form very stiff peaks.
Spoon egg whites on batter.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and remove.
Put custard in between.

title: lemon raspberry muffins
directions: Combine and mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend well half and half, oil, lemon extract and eggs.
Add to above mixture.
Use raspberries or try a different berry minus any liquid.
Fold berries and poppy seed into mixture.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 23 minutes or until golden brown.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cauliflower, cheese and bacon in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and then toss with first mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together all ingredients except brown gravy mix.
Shape into 6 - 8 patties.
Brown in electric skillet on both sides. Place patties into 9 x 13 pan sprayed with pan spray.
Prepare gravy mix according to directions.
Pour over patties.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: cottage pudding(for over cake)
directions: Cook to clear syrup and remove from heat. Add dollop of butter (about 1/4 cup) and 1 teaspoon vanilla or lemon extract and stir in rapidly. Serve over cake or gingerbread.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
(I use milk instead of water.)
Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Pour condensed milk over warm cake.
Spread approximately 1/3 cup caramel topping over condensed milk.
Let cake cool completely, then frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with crushed Butterfingers.
Store in refrigerator.

title: phyllo apple-pear pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Place fruit and next 8 ingredients in heavy saucepan. Stir and cook over medium heat 20 minutes or until fruit is tender. Allow to cool slightly. Spoon into 9-inch pie plate sprayed with baking spray. Lay 1 sheet phyllo over filling; brush with melted spread and sprinkle with sugar. Continue with 3 more sheets. Gather edges of phyllo to make a ruffled edge; spray edge with baking spray. Cut slits in top of pastry for steam to escape. Can garnish by cutting shapes out of fifth phyllo sheet. Bake 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Brown beef in margarine.
Add onion; add all ingredients except cheese.
Bake 15 minutes, covered; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Saute diced onions and bell peppers in butter.
Brown meat. Add salt, pepper, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Add diced onions and peppers, tomato sauce and soups. Simmer at least 1 hour.
Cook over low heat.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add Bisquick mix; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 6-8 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw the potatoes and place in 2-quart casserole dish. Add soup, sour cream, onion and Cheddar cheese to potatoes.
Stir gently to mix well.
Top with bread crumbs and additional Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak across grain into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside.
Heat oil in large pan or wok.
Add beef; toss on high heat until browned.
If meat is not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn up heat.
Add vegetables; toss until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan.
Stir until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: each peach pie
directions: Put sliced peaches in unbaked pie shell. Pour mixture over peaches. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: english toffee
directions: Put all ingredients together in heavy pan; stir all during cooking.
Cook over high heat until mixture turns light brown. After it comes to full boil, cook about 5 or 6 minutes.
Pour at once on tin foil.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, nuts and apples.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs, oil and flour.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and then put in the freezer; keep in freezer until served.
Also, keep any leftovers in freezer.

title: teri's party ball
directions: Mix all together and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: uncle lee's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a square Pyrex dish, melt margarine in oven.
Remove from oven and cool.
Combine meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs, milk and margarine.
Pour mixture into the dish where the margarine was melted and bake in oven for 45 minutes.
Do not overbake as it will cause the bread to be dry.

title: corn flake chicken
directions: Coat each piece in Miracle Whip and roll in corn flake and sesame seed mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours with lid off for first 45 minutes, on for the next hour and off for the final 15 minutes.
Best if chicken is not layered.
Very moist chicken.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl.
Beat slowly until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: lena culp's marinated carrots
directions: Combine ingredients from tomato soup on, heat to boiling. Pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Marinate 12 hours.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: corn pone(sweet corn bread)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Can be made in muffin pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in buttered pans.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Preheat oven on 350°.
Combine whole wheat flour with next 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in the center and add eggs, pineapple, bananas and oil in the well.
Stir just until moistened. Spoon into greased and floured muffin cups.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Over medium heat, cook onion and meat until brown, stirring often.
Add tomatoes, soup, paprika, cayenne, bay leaf and chili powder.
Simmer 1 hour, adding water if it gets too thick.
Stir in salt and kidney beans; do not drain beans.
Heat thoroughly. Makes about 6 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon with onion in large saucepan until bacon is crisp and onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in flour.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add 2 cups water, potato, sage and bay leaf.
Simmer, covered for 10 to 15 minutes or just until potatoes are tender. Remove bay leaf.
Add creamer, 1 cup boiling water, cheese, corn, salt and pepper.
Heat just to the boiling point, stirring until cheese is melted.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Garnish with parsley and chives.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marge's white chili
directions: Mix all together and cook on low in crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Save 2 egg whites for meringue.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Cool and pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in hot oven.

title: beef spread
directions: Cream the cheese and milk together.
Add sour cream and beat. Shred dried beef.
Crisp 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans in 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir 1 cup into mixture.
Place all ingredients in small casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve piping hot on crackers.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix batter and bake as directed on the box.

When done, cool and then turn out onto waxed paper, top side up to cool completely. Set aside five pkg. of frozen coconut and milk from two fresh coconuts (punch holes in coconuts and drain milk into a measuring cup).
Strain and set aside to use last.

title: fourteen karat cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Turn mixture out into three greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with the Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, melt oleo.
Let pan cool (this is important).
Add cake mix and 2 eggs.
Mix well, will be very thick.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Set aside.
In another bowl, cream the cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs, cream again.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Pour over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mildred's french toast
directions: Mix with a hand beater.
Dip slice of bread in batter.
Drop in deep, hot oil.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Lightly brown onion and celery in butter.
Add flour and mix smooth.
Add chicken broth, milk, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook slowly until thick; add pimentos, eggs, chicken, mushrooms and peas.
Simmer until thick.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: aunt ella's molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard.
Add molasses and water.
Stir in enough flour so that dough does not stick.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You will need nonstick cooking spray and brown paper grocery sack.
Spray bag with nonstick spray and put popcorn in it.

title: macadamia orange cheese cake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
With the bak of a spoon, press onto bottom and sides (not on rim) of a 9-inch pie pan. Refrigerate while preparing filling.
Chop 1/2 cup of the Macadamia nuts; set aside.

title: chicken pasta soup
directions: Cook chicken, onions and garlic in the oil in large saucepan over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except pasta.
Bring to boil.
Stir in pasta.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until pasta is tender, about 12 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Sift together the flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening and butter until crumbly.
Mix vinegar with cold water.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir with fork until dough clings together. Divide into 2 portions.
Roll on floured surface.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts at bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top each piece with Monterey Jack.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 can white wine (no water). Heat on top of stove until smooth.
Pour onto chicken. Spread 1 box stuffing on top of cheese, bread crumbs first, then seasoning package.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Drain all fruits; combine fruits* in
a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, melted butter and curry; stir well and spoon over fruit.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Good served with any entree.
We serve this on Christmas morning with Laura's Eggs and Grits Souffle.

title: luau racks of lamb
directions: Place lamb, fat side up, in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert a meat thermometer into thickest portion of meat without touching bone.
Roast, uncovered, in a 375° oven for about 45 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 125°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour cream and milk over bread cubes in large bowl.
Beat egg yolks and 1 cup sugar until light.
Stir in raisins and vanilla. Stir egg yolk mixture into bread mixture.
Let stand 10 minutes. Beat egg whites; add 3 tablespoons of sugar until stiff but not dry.
Fold egg whites into bread mixture.
Pour into 2-quart casserole; set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Add it to the potatoes.
Add everything else, except the cornflakes.
Mix well.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in large bowl.
Add milk, salt, butter, eggs and 1/2 cup sugar; mix well.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease surface.
Let rise in warm place for 5 to 6 hours or in refrigerator overnight.
Shape as desired or put into greased muffin pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs. Slowly add powdered sugar while mixing.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour on top.

title: peanut butter fingers(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Sprinkle with semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar, peanut butter and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Spread chocolate evenly.
Drizzle with peanut butter mixture.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: peanut butter chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In a large bowl, beat butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients until well blended. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls. Bake 10-12 minutes for soft cookies and 12-14 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: baked stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half long way.
Remove all seeds.
Brown hamburger; drain grease; add all ingredients and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Poke holes (halfway) in bottom of each zucchini half. Add melted butter in each half.
Add ingredient mixture and wrap each half in aluminum foil.
Add a little water between foil and zucchini.
Place sliced Mozzarella cheese on top and close foil. Bake until zucchini is soft; about 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: death-by-chocolate dessert
directions: Bake brownies according to directions.
Cool.
Break up brownies and pour kahlua over.
Set aside.
Whip chocolate mousse according to directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces.
Put 1/2 brownies into glass truffle bowl.
Cover with 1/2 mousse. Layer with 1/2 the candy and 1/2 whipped topping.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Add hot water to gelatin, stir until dissolved.
Let cool but do not gel.
Add mayonnaise, onion flakes, sour cream, diced celery, chopped eggs and corned beef which has been separated with fork as it comes from can.
Combine all ingredients and stir lightly.
Pour into 2-quart rectangular glass dish.
Refrigerate until gelled.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then roll in extra pecans. Refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers.
(Can use light cream cheese.)

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix cornmeal, creamed corn, soda, salt, eggs, milk and oil.
Add chopped onions and peppers. Mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle ground beef over top of mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnabons
directions: Grease sides and bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan generously with Crisco shortening.
Sprinkle raisins and nuts over bottom of pan.
Place frozen dinner rolls over raisins and nuts (four rolls across and six rows altogether).
