Sprinkle the butterscotch pudding over all the rolls.

title: baked pineapple with cheese
directions: Drain pineapple.
Keep 3 tablespoons of juice.
Add grated cheese and pineapple.
Mix well.
Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: glenna's noodles(never fail)
directions: Cook in broth (ham, beef or chicken).
Mix the ingredients together, then roll flat and cut into noodles.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: In a large mixing
bowl cream margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes between each one or until mixture is smooth.
Blend in
powdered
sugar very slowly.
Add melted chocolate and continue to
blend
until smooth.
Pour into pie shells and chill
overnight.
Garnish
with
whipped
topping. Makes 2 pies.

title: a sweet bird
directions: Dry chicken with paper towel.
Mix other ingredients and dip pieces in to coat well.
Place chicken in a shallow baking pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Baste once or twice.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick.
Put Bisquick mixture around strip of cheese and jalapeno pepper.
Coat with Shake 'n Bake. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Blend all ingredients, except beef.
Add beer and stir.
Cut steak across grain into 1/4-inch slices.
Put into a tight fitting container.
Pour marinade over meat.
Refrigerate overnight, turning once or twice.
Discard marinade and pat meat with paper towels to remove excess moisture; salt and pepper to taste.
Put on skewers, meat hanging down.
Dry in a smoker or in the oven on lowest setting with oven door cracked open so moisture can escape. Cook until desired dryness, not brittle.

title: pickled peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix jello and gelatine and chill slightly until thickened.
Stir in peach pickles, pecans, pickle juice and pineapple.
Pour into one large bowl or individual molds and chill.

title: fig bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, light brown sugar, and melted margarine and press in bottom of pan.
Save remaining
1/2 for top.
Mix figs and white sugar and spread over the bottom half of mixture. Cover with remaining mix and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy saucepan.
Add chopped onions and minced clove of garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add redskin kidney beans, tomato sauce, salt, black pepper and chili powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour into pan. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bacon and egg brunch item
directions: Fry bacon, leaving slices limp so they can be molded; drain. In a Teflon cupcake pan, line bacon in all 12 wells.
Crack an egg and place inside the circle of bacon.
Bake at 350° until eggs are cooked (about 30 minutes).
Egg whites will be firm.
If yolk is runny, continue to cook until desired firmness.
Perfect for breakfast brunch.

title: delicious treats
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and melted oleo together and pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 2 cups of coconut on top of crust mixture.
Press lightly.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of coconut.
Next, put on the chopped nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: pressure cooker honey baked beans
directions: Wash beans, then cover with water.
Soak beans overnight. Drain.
Brown salt pork in pressure cooker.
Add chopped onion and stir.
Add beans, ketchup, honey and dry mustard, brown sugar, salt and pepper and water.
Cover.
Set control at 15 pounds pressure about 20 to 25 minutes after pressure regulator jiggles. Reduce pressure normally.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, water, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger.
Marinate wings for 3 hours to overnight.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Bake at 350°.

title: easy cheese quiche
directions: Spread grated cheese in bottom of 8-inch pie plate.
Blend remaining ingredients and add to cheese.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry bran pancakes(original recipe)
directions: You will need cooking spray.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat the cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of the whipped topping; spread over crust.
Using 3 1/2 cups cold milk, prepare pudding as directed on package.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops of peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Mix raw beef with onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Divide evenly into peppers. Arrange peppers upright and snugly in a 3-quart casserole dish. Blend soup and water until smooth; pour over peppers.
Cover; microwave at High for approximately 28 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Re-cover; let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: nanny's meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into 1/2-inch meatballs.
Bake on baking sheet in 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, turning twice. Drain on paper towels or put in crock-pot in brown gravy.
May be served over wide noodles.
Excellent for parties!

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together over low heat.
Cool. Mix eggs and sugar; add flour and chocolate mixture.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 3 aluminum foil pans, greased with margarine.
Bake at 325° for about 35 to 45 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Pie will set as it cools and then may be frozen.

title: filling for chocolate fried pies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa. Add vanilla. Stir in just enough pet milk to make everything stick together. Filling must be very stiff. Roll out pie crust or canned biscuits to make a large circle. Dip fingers in cold water and dampen the edge of half of each circle of biscuit. Add one rounded tsp. chocolate filling and half a pat of butter. Fold in half and with teeth of fork dipped in flour, press around edges to seal. The cold water and pressing edges keeps filling from running into the oil when frying.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion and garlic.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt. Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar and vinegar.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup in pan for 2 to 3 minutes (lukewarm).
Do not dilute.
Put envelope of Knox gelatine in small custard cup with 2 tablespoons of water and stir.
Fold in with the soup mixture and stir.
Fold in the cream cheese until melted.
Stir in mayo.
Stir in remainder of ingredients.
Put in mold or place in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Spread on crust and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely, then mix well pudding, milk, pumpkin and cinnamon.
Pour over cooled mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, pecans and 1 egg with hands if necessary.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend everything together and refrigerate.

title: nashville fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and Baker's chocolate together.
Add all other ingredients together.
Mix chocolate and margarine mixture with other ingredients.
Bake in greased pie pan for 25 minutes at 350° or until firm in center.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Serve hot or cold. Good to eat with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hawaiian baked mochi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and spread into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: yum-a-setta casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions and add cream of chicken soup; set aside.
Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain oil.
Add brown sugar and tomato soup with all previous ingredients to make mixture, except noodles and cheese. Layer noodles and beef mixture, then cheese.
Make 2 layers ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue for 25 people
directions: Fry hamburger but not until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and boil for 30 minutes.
After boiling, add catsup.
Combine with meat.
This makes a thick barbecue.
Best if made a day ahead of serving.

title: sugar free raisin bars
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook raisins, water, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg until margarine is melted; continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Spread into an 8-inch square baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 16 bars.

title: cream tacos
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Put whipping cream, sliced Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Hormel chilli into crock-pot on low heat and cook for 2 hours or longer until thickens.
Serve with 1 bag Doritos chips, chopped onions, tomatoes, lettuce, American cheese (shredded) and sour cream.
Put Doritos on plate. Top with hamburger mixture, onions, tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and sour cream.

title: cucumber salad(sour without vinegar)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside 1 hour.
Then add sugar or Sweet 'N Low and lemon juice.
Mix all together and put in refrigerator.

title: spinach salad
directions: Take stems off spinach; wash and put in plastic bag in the refrigerator to get cold and crisp.
Two eggs are sliced for the top of salad, the other 2 are chopped and mixed with the remaining ingredients for the dressing.
Just before serving, pour over crisp spinach; garnish with sliced eggs and serve.

title: chocolate lovers frosting
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat 1 cup of sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and vanilla until smooth.
Add rest of sugar until smooth.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: In a 4-quart pot, cook mostaccioli according to the package directions, adding the peas for the last 3 minutes of cooking time.
Drain in a colander and rinse the mixture with cold water. Transfer the pasta and peas to a large bowl and add the celery, ham, mushrooms, tomato and carrots.
Add the dressing and toss. Makes 6 servings.

title: bullets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, beat together butter, granulated sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour until well blended.
If necessary, work with fingers until the dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 15 or 17 minutes in preheated oven at 350° or until golden brown.
Remove from sheets.
Cool on racks while still slightly warm.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 30 (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: apple crisp
directions: In casserole dish, spread apple filling.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with yellow cake mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and cover with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° until brown (35 to 40 minutes).

title: blondies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix together creamed butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, breaking vermicelli into smaller pieces.
Add two tomato soup cans of water or enough for desired consistency. Simmer for about one hour.

title: easy chicken appetizers
directions: Mix buttermilk and dressing mix.
Pour over chicken, cover and let stand overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and turmeric.
Dip chicken in dry mixture and deep fry until golden brown.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, salt and mustard.
Mix well and add milk slowly. Add lemon juice. Cook until semi-thick.
Pour over crab.
Bake in a well buttered casserole.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.
Place fruit in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over fruit. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well; store in refrigerator.
Wonderful with shrimp or crab meat.

title: oven-baked chicken kiev
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add chives, lemon peel, lemon juice and pepper; mix.
Shape 3/4 cup of this mixture into six 2-inch sticks.
Freeze firm.
Place chicken between sheets of waxed paper; pound to flatten.
Salt lightly.
Place 1 butter stick on each.
Roll up; secure with wooden picks.
Combine egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Coat chicken with flour.
Dip in egg; coat with crumbs.
In skillet, heat remaining butter mixture.
Add chicken; cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, turning to brown all sides.
Bake in shallow baking pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of crushed Ritz crackers on top of melted margarine in bottom of casserole dish.
Cut chicken in small pieces and mix with other ingredients.
Pour in dish on top of margarine and crackers.
Top with remaining crackers and cook at 350° for about 25 or 30 minutes.

title: taco pie(appetizer)
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in attractive, shallow dish or 9-inch pie plate.
Serve with tortilla chips at room temperature (may be made ahead and kept in refrigerator).
Serves 6.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add rice, almonds, chives and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until almonds are golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Squeeze juice out of kraut, chop celery, pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight; stir once or twice, if possible.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add Kool-Aid until it is the color you want.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Add cold water, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Add liter of ginger ale to each average size punch bowl.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Combine with eggs and oleo. Add syrup and vanilla.
Beat
with
a
rotary egg beater until well mixed.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat
to 325° and bake 40 minutes or until pie is firm.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese until Jell-O is dissolved and well mixed.
Drain all fruit very well; mix with cottage cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate several hours. Can be used as a salad or dessert.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; chill until thickened.
Add celery, nuts and sauce, which has been broken into pieces.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm, several hours or overnight.
Unmold when needed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry salad(quick and easy)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and partly thawed strawberries.
Stir until strawberries are melted.
Put half of mixture into 9x13 pan.
Let set.
Spread sour cream on top, sprinkle with pecans, let set.
Spoon other half of mixture on top and let set.
It works better if you let the sour cream set out for awhile and then stir it real well.

title: mexicali meat pie
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; break into large pieces.
Chill 1/3 cup drippings until firm.
Brown hamburger in large skillet; drain. Stir in corn, green pepper, onion, cornmeal, oregano, chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Prepare crust (recipe follows).
Place meat mix in pastry lined pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Combine egg, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Spread on pie.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Cook pineapple with Jell-O.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese, pecans and whipping cream.
Chill.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven.
Cook rice, meanwhile, in oleo in skillet.
Saute celery and onions until tender; grease casserole.
Place rice at bottom; top with celery mixture.
Season chuck.
Brown in skillet, then arrange on top of celery.
Combine soup with water.
Pour over chuck.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: prune cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then 325° for 45 minutes.
May be baked in a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: overnight blueberry muffins
directions: The night before, sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat butter with sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and ending with the flour mixture.
Beat just until smooth.
Gently fold in blueberries. Scoop 1/4 cup batter into greased muffin cups Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 18.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and blend together.
Mix the dressing; pour over vegetables.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in a pan over low heat.
Add sugar, cocoa, vanilla and milk.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add oats. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool and eat.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve in hollowed out round bread loaf.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 of butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: nice crust chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with mustard; set aside. In large shallow dish, mix together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Roll the chicken, in the bread crumb mixture to coat.
Place chicken in a large, lightly greased baking pan, meaty side up.
Drizzle chicken with the melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes or until fork-tender.
Arrange chicken on a serving dish and top with sour cream.

title: nana nonie's applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour or more.
Makes 2 loaf cakes.
Grease and flour pans.

title: salad eggs
directions: Slice eggs in halves and put yolks in a bowl.
Fill the halves with tuna salad, chicken salad, ham salad or pimento cheese. Sprinkle yolk crumbs on the halves.

title: butter biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in petite muffin pans or drop on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: honey bun coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Next mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 over batter and swirl with a knife.
Top with remaining batter and other half of cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: nut torte
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Blend in 3/4 cup sugar.
Add 2 teaspoons either vanilla or almond flavoring.
Bake at 350° between 30 to 45 minutes.
Good with whipped cream or a glaze made by heating apricot or raspberry jam.

title: macaroni ham salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Rinse with cold water.
Add ham and remaining ingredients.
Toss and chill for at least four hours.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender.
Drain and put in baking dish. Crumble corned beef over top of cabbage.
Put Cheddar cheese over corned beef.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients; mix well.
Good for party snacks with assorted crackers.

title: butternut cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl cream butter and 3/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Add flavorings and mix until fluffy.
In small bowl combine flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients and pecans to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until firm to touch and brown on bottoms.
Cool, then roll in 3/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Yields about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in bowl with fork.
Stir in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla completely.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: new york-style egg cream
directions: Pour milk and syrup into a tall glass.
Stir.
Add enough club soda to reach rim of glass.
Stir top with whipped cream.
Also add sprinkles and a cherry if desired.

title: chipped beef in popovers
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan.
Stir meat in butter for three minutes.
Mix soup and milk, stir in sauce pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until creamy.
Stir in cheese, parsley, and pimento. Reduce heat and cook 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve chipped beef sauce over split hot popover.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas with sugar, then add all together.
Can use mixer to blend together good.
If you use mixer, add pecans last.
Cook in Bundt pan at 250° until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per instructions on package.
Add all of the ingredients, except crackers.
Crumble crackers on top of mixture and dot with butter so as to make crackers crunchy.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: baked beans
directions: Saute peppers and onions in butter until tender.
Add beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for one hour, stirring often.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Store in air tight container.

title: tuna with orange and ginger
directions: In a bowl, combine marinade juice, ginger, oil, salt, pepper and powdered garlic.
In oven-proof glass baking dish, place tuna in single layer and pour juice mixture over it.
Let marinade for about 45 minutes.
Pour out all but small amount of marinade. Preheat broiler and place tuna under broiler or grill and cook thoroughly 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Heat remaining marinade until it bubbles.
Pour over tuna and sprinkle with chopped scallions, just before serving.

title: homemade fruit cocktail(glaze)
directions: When all fruits are drained and in bowl, mix pudding and pineapple juice (will be thick).
Pour over fruits.
Stir with hand or large spoon to mix well, until glaze covers all fruit.
Place in covered container.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain canned vegetables and mix together in very large mixing bowl.
In small microwavable bowl, cook onion, celery and pepper, covered, on High with 1 teaspoon water (to soften, you may want to saute).
Mix vegetables with all other ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour into large oblong Pyrex dish well-greased with margarine or cooking spray.
Crush cracker stack and spread evenly over casserole top.
Melt margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until bubbles and top is golden crispy brown.

title: beef stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, egg, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper; stir well.
Cook cabbage leaves in boiling salted water 5 to 8 minutes or until just tender; drain.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf; fold ends over and fasten with wooden pick.
Saute onion in butter in a large skillet until tender, but not brown.
Add tomato soup and remaining ingredients, stirring well; simmer 10 minutes.
Place cabbage rolls in the tomato mixture; cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour, salt, brown sugar and margarine to a crumbly stage.
Place layer of oat mixture in a well greased pan, then one layer of cranberry sauce.
Repeat layers until all is used.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients to boiling.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour hot sugar mixture and 1 teaspoon vanilla in baking pan then add the flour mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Cake will come to top and sauce will form on the bottom.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
(Add nuts and raisins if desired.) Pour into greased and floured containers and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaf pans or 4 pound coffee cans.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beating after each one.
Gradually add flour and soda to the creamed mixture, alternating with the buttermilk.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: tomato, hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Combine meat and onions with cooked, drained noodles, cheese, soup, water, peppers, chili sauce, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Mix well and turn into 9x13 baking dish.
Combine bread pieces with melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.

title: roast beef
directions: Sprinkle each side of roast with listed seasoning, sauce and onions.
Place in browning bag and follow directions of manufacturer of bag.
Place in oven at 300° in pan and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending upon doneness desired.
Beef makes own natural gravy that may be used as is or, if preferred, can be thickened as desired.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with juice.
Combine avocado mixture, cream cheese, onions and seasonings; mixing well until blended.
Stir in tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oven-barbecued spareribs
directions: Arrange pork spareribs in large open roasting pan in one layer. Roast spareribs in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender. Meanwhile, in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat grapefruit juice and remaining ingredients to boiling.
Cool 1 minute, stirring mixture constantly, to prevent sticking.
During last 30 minutes of roasting, brush ribs frequently with grapefruit mixture.

title: burkauts
directions: Brown hamburger, cabbage and onions with a lot of salt and pepper. Simmer for an hour or two. Use a roll size amount of dough and roll out on floured board 1-1 1/2 inches thick. In the middle of the dough put a large scoop of hamburger mix. Fold over and bake at 350 degrees, until golden brown. Take out and brush with butter. Enjoy!

title: taco salad
directions: Toss hot meat mixture (ground beef cooked with taco seasoning) with remaining chilled ingredients and serve.

title: ilah's casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck; add onion and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese) and put in a casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until heated through and through.

title: wanda's bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in
Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: fresh fried fish
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Put crushed crackers in a separate bowl. Dip fish in eggs, salt, then in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot cast iron skillet with oil.

title: giant's holiday bake
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe casserole combine vegetables, soup, milk and half of the onion rings.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes (or bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes) until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with remaining onion rings before serving.
Yields 5 servings.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Melt sugar, butter and dates until well mixed.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Shape and roll in coconut.

title: christiana campbell's tavern sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes.
Beat in egg and lemon peel.
Stir in dry ingredients and milk.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Fill tins 3/4 full; sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 400°.
These are nice baked in mini tins, also!

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread half over bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Press down (not too tight).
Spread cranberry sauce over it.
Spread rest of mixture over sauce.
Pat down.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until it sets.

title: aunt jean's cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Add butter or shortening, milk and eggs.
Mix well, but don't overmix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together meal, flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder.
In separate bowl, beat quickly the milk, eggs and oil; add to dry mixture.
Bake at 425° in sizzling hot 8 x 10-inch pan or iron frying pan.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Add dry milk and sugar to water.
Mix well; set in pan of hot water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Store in refrigerator. Equals one can of milk.
Use just as any canned milk (sweetened condensed milk) is called for.

title: cantaloupe parfait
directions: Alternate layers of strawberries and melon balls in 6 parfait glasses.
Chill.
Boil together sugar and water until the syrup spins a thread (230°).
Stir in honey, cinnamon and rum.
Cool and pour about 2 tablespoons over the fruit in each parfait glass. Decorate with mint sprigs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put a layer of potatoes in a well-greased casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add a layer of onions and a layer of cabbage.
Brown pork chops quickly.
Remove and place on top of vegetables in casserole.
Blend in soup with 1 can water and chop fat and heat.
Pour over casserole.
Bake uncovered 1/2 hour in 350° oven, then cover and continue to bake an hour longer.

title: tuna salad - luncheon style
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Serves 8.

title: home style lasagna
directions: *Cook sausage at 350° in open pan.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Add the carrots, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend all together and bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: ham chowder
directions: Combine corn, tomatoes, broth, celery, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove from heat.
Melt butter; blend in flour and stir in milk. Cook and stir until thickened and boiling.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Add cheese, peppers and ham.
Simmer until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: indian stew
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes on low heat.
Serve with saltines.

title: mexican buffet
directions: Start buffet with Fritos.
Cover with rice (cover Fritos well) and chili (cover rice).
Add grated cheese, shredded lettuce, chopped tomato, chopped onions and chopped green olives.
Over this pour El Paso taco sauce.
Add coconut and pecans (these are optional).

title: canadian cheese soup(secret shortcut makes it fast and easy)
directions: Mix potato slices, cheese sauce mix, broth, water, carrots, celery in 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat, add cream and parsley.
Serves 6-9.

title: creamy mushroom rice
directions: Crumble the mushrooms and soak them in warm water for 30 minutes.
Drain well and reserve mushroom water.

title: puffed broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Mix soup, milk, flour, mustard and pepper, stirring over medium heat until almost boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in beaten egg yolks and broccoli until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form when beaters are lifted.
Fold into broccoli mixture.
Pour into prepared
dish. Bake 50 minutes or until top is golden and puffy and an inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter, blend in flour, then remove from heat. Stir in milk, return to heat to thicken.
Stir in salt, pepper sauce, marjoram and cheese.
Add potatoes to sauce.
Bake in casserole for 25 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with paprika.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice in blender and blend on high for 15 seconds.
Add crushed ice to fill blender and blend until smooth.
Makes 12 cups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Refrigerate first.
Then roll on floured area.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes 7 to 7 1/2 dozen heart shaped cookies.

title: pound cake sandwich(kid's recipe)
directions: Cut 12 (2/3-inch thick) slices of pound cake.
Place 6 slices of pound cake on your work surface.
Spread on one slice 5 tablespoons of softened ice cream.
Smooth the edges of the sandwiches, if necessary.
Place another slice of pound cake on top; press down.
Wrap in plastic wrap and place in freezer. Repeat with remaining slices.
Serve within a month.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and add all other ingredients, heating cheese with soups to melt.
Heat to serve.

title: candied yams
directions: Cut potatoes long ways.
Cook on top of stove in a little water with sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Cover and let tenderize and cook down.
If they don't candy enough
add " a little more sugar, shaking, but not stirring.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix preceding ingredients and serve with following dressing.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chickens, for sauce; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cut broiler chickens in half and remove skin.
Place chicken on low fire.
Turn and baste with sauce until very brown.
Cook 1 to 2 hours, depending on size of chickens.
Use tongs to prevent puncture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except the catsup thoroughly.
Shape into loaf and put into loaf pan.
Spread catsup on top of meat loaf. Bake at 400° for approximately one hour.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Flour meat in a mixture of flour, garlic powder, salt, pepper and paprika. Brown meat in oleo. Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add all ingredients to meat.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Leave the lid off during the last 1/2 hour of cooking time.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, water and butter.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes, stirring halfway through.
Blend cornstarch with 3 tablespoons water and stir into hot sugar mixture.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice and lemon peel.
Gradually add egg yolks, taking care to avoid overcooking.
Cook mixture 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Cool and pour into pie shell.

title: amish brown sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In the pie shell, place the brown sugar, flour and salt.
Mix with your fingers.
Pour the evaporated milk over the flour and sugar, but do not stir or mix this in.
Dot with butter and cinnamon liberally over all.
Bake for 50 minutes or until the filling just bubbles up in the middle. The filling will never completely set, but that's the way it's supposed to be.
This pie is best eaten at room temperature.

title: golden slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Be sure to mix well.

title: red lobster biscuit recipe
directions: Mix the butter, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Brush evenly over batter.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 400° until nicely browned.
Makes 12.
Hope you enjoy!

title: cheese filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions; drain and cool. Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with 2 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place shells in a single layer in dish.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with additional cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crispy crunch ice cream
directions: In skillet, melt butter and add sugar.
Heat slowly.
Stir until blended.
Add corn flakes; toss to coat well.
Remove from heat and add peanuts.
Cool.
Stir into softened ice cream.
Pour into freezer tray and re-freeze.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chinese broccoli and beef
directions: Mix beef with soy sauce, sherry, sugar and Accent.
Marinate. Cut broccoli 2 inches long.
Stir-fry in 2 tablespoons oil in hot skillet.
Add salt. Stir until done but still crisp.
Take out. Put rest of oil in skillet.
Add onions and beef and stir-fry briefly.
Return broccoli.
Serve over rice.

title: beefy barbecue beans
directions: In deep 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add pork and beans and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until thickened.
Serve on hamburger buns or corn bread or as a side dish.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine eggs, cooking oil and pumpkin.
Stir all dry ingredients together.
Add egg mixture.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: russian dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in container.
Mix thoroughly and put in jar to store in refrigerator.

title: pecan bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Sift the flour and spices.
Add to mix.
Add baby food and mix well.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into greased tube pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mexican pepper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well.
It is actually better 2 or 3 days after preparation.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pease pudding
directions: Wash peas thoroughly.
Bring water to a boil and drop peas in. Reduce heat and simmer until peas can be mashed easily (about 1 hour).
Remove from heat and mash well to a puree.
Return peas to the pan and add salt, butter and seasoning, stirring constantly.
Transfer to a serving dish.
Serve warm.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and add first 8 ingredients.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer uncovered until thick (approximately 1 hour).
Stir occasionally.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut, rinse and cover with water.
Let stand and drain again.
Add vegetables and dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: sarah's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar thoroughly.
Sift flour once. Add dry ingredients, then sift 4 more times.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients altogether, then push the boneless chicken into the mixture.
Then roll in the corn bread stuffing. Pour 1/4 cup of butter over this and cover; let this bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Then uncover; pour more butter or margarine over chicken and bake 15 more minutes.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix well pineapple, sugar and sour cream; add instant pudding and then put in graham cracker crusts.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with pineapple tidbits and maraschino cherries.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: "can't stop eating it" caramel corn
directions: In large saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring over medium heat.
Stirring constantly, boil until mixture reaches 260° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and quickly but thoroughly pour over popped corn after stirring in baking soda.
Be sure all kernels are coated.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times during baking.
Turn out on waxed paper; cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with your favorite snack cracker.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Add no water; mix chicken and soup.
Fold in vegetables.

title: 5 spice, beef and rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Place in baking dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: millie's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Boil water, cocoa and margarine and pour over flour; add eggs.
Dissolve buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla together.
Mix all together.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch cake dish.

title: turkey noodle bake(makes 8, 1 c servings)
directions: Pre heat oven to 375 degrees. In a medium saucepan, combine milk, flour, and bouillon; stir until flour is dissolved. Over medium heat, cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese. Coat a 2 qt baking dish with veg. spray. Spoon mixture into dish. Top with cheese. Cover, and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Mix the two sets of ingredients.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch freezer safe container.
Freeze for 2 to 3 hours.
Take out.
Cut into squares.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks in freezer.

title: layered salad
directions: In a nonmetal, oblong pan, layer as follows:
lettuce, celery, onion, green pepper and peas.
In a bowl, combine Miracle Whip and sugar.
Spoon onto the layered ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
May be mixed before serving or serve as is.

title: salmon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set for a few minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gourmet rice pudding
directions: Measure rice, boiling water and salt into top of double boiler. Cook over rapidly boiling water until rice is tender, about 40 minutes.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, margarine and raisins. Cook, stirring frequently, over boiling water until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate yum yums
directions: Melt shortening, chocolate and brown sugar, stirring until smooth.
Cool.
Add egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour into a shallow greased pan, about 10 1/2 x 15-inches.
Sprinkle with ground nuts and coconut.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, about 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.
Makes about 36 squares.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fireball salad
directions: Drain pineapple, then mix all ingredients together. Pour into casserole dish and freeze.

title: wilted spinach salad(serves 6)
directions: Chop the cleaned spinach.
Remove the pits from the olives. Combine all ingredients, except the olive oil in a metal bowl. Heat the olive oil in a saucepan until almost smoking.
Pour the hot oil over the salad and toss quickly.
Add more vinegar if necessary.

title: beef pot roast gourmet
directions: Place roast in a heavy roasting pan and add everything except the artichokes, onions, carrots and wine.
Cover; place in oven at 275° for two hours.
Add artichokes, onions, carrots and wine and continue to cook for one hour or until meat is tender.
Slice the meat and arrange on platter surrounded by the vegetables.
Keep hot while cooking down pan juices to serve as gravy.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: low-fat chocolate icing
directions: Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Allow a rolling boil for 1 minute.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water (save water).
Prepare rice according to box directions in chicken water.
Mix soups and milk together. Dice chicken.
Layer chicken, rice and soup mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add almonds; bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: mac-n-cheese
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni as package directs.
Drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend in milk. Cook and stir until thickened.
Mix cheeses together.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Add remaining cheese to sauce; stir until melted.
Mix in macaroni and parsley.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish, top with reserved cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Garnish if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no bake strawberry patch
directions: Combine graham crackers, sugar and butter, then press into large baking dish.
Mix jello, water and strawberries.
Set aside to congeal slightly.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip, walnuts and sugar.
Pour onto crumb crust.
Top with thickened strawberries.

title: ham rolls
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slice.
Lay onion on edge of ham and roll up like a jelly roll.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes and slice into pinwheels.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Beat whipping cream in chilled 1 1/2-pint bowl until stiff. Fold horseradish and salt.
Makes 1 cup sauce; 25 calories per tablespoon.
Delicious topping for beef, ham and pork.

title: golden ham pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add baking powder, ham, pepper, milk and cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: cabbage slaw dressing
directions: Heat all ingredients together and pour over shredded cabbage.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add liquids and cook over medium heat until thickened and mixture leaves side of pan.
Pour onto wax paper.
Let cool slightly, then knead until mixture is smooth.
Store in airtight container.

title: chili cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef and onions; drain.
Stir in other ingredients, except Worcestershire and cheese.
Spread into pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Add Worcestershire and cheese; bake 10 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Roll into balls and bake at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; let dissolve. Combine all ingredients and let chill for 4 hours or overnight.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix ingredients until it resembles batter.
Dip fish in batter, then fry.

title: pixy pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Beat thoroughly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Pour into pan.
Now pour peaches into mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown chicken in butter.
Make sauce of soup, sour cream and sherry.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Put chicken in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and pour sauce over it.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickled okra
directions: You will need 1-gallon or quart jars.

title: old-time corn relish
directions: Chop all and put in pan.
Put 1 quart vinegar over it.
Let stand a few minutes, then add another quart of vinegar and soak for 20 minutes and can.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with rotary beater.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Parboil onion and hamburg.
Add beef, onion, tomatoes and diced Longhorn cheese to cooked spaghetti.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: bewitching blueberry pancakes
directions: As you stir in the blueberries (this is the magic part) say three times:

title: grandma's boiled pot pie (chicken or beef)
directions: Combine flour, salt, egg yolk and milk as needed to form dough ball (as pie dough).
Flour surface and roll dough round and thin as possible.
Cut dough into 2 1/2 to 3-inch squares.
Remove meat from broth.
Bring to a full boil and drop flakes one at a time. Do not drop on top of each flake; go from one side of pot to the other until each flake is wet.
Reduce heat; cook 20 minutes or until flakes are dropping below broth.
Be sure heat stays at slow boil.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes or to desired thickness.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs. Place in a greased casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 6.
Optional: Cheese sprinkled on top.

title: bacon cheese appetizer pie
directions: Roll pastry into a 13 1/2 inch circle. Fit into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9 inch spring form pan. Lightly prick the bottom. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add eggs and milk; beat until smooth. Add the Swiss cheese, onions, bacon, salt, pepper and cayenne; mix well. Pour into the crust. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 20 minutes. Remove sides of pan. Cut into thin slices; serve warm. Yield: 16-20 servings.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place length of foil on flat surface.
In large bowl, beat shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla on medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg; beat well.
Stir together flour, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, beating on low speed just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheet to foil.
Cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: sherrill's new england peach cobbler
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a buttered dish and dot with margarine.
Sift the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add the melted margarine, egg and milk.
Beat well and add to peach mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: green chili cheese dip
directions: Combine undiluted soup and cheese in a saucepan over low heat. Stir often until cheese is melted to prevent burning.
Add chopped green chilies.
Serve warm with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: florida orange meringue pie
directions: Combine orange juice, sections, grated rind, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook on low heat until clear.
Add a little hot mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and butter or margarine.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Be sure filling and shell are both hot or both cold.
Cover filling with meringue. Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: root beer float cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 1 1/4 cups root beer, oil and eggs.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes or by hand for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack. In a mixing bowl, combine whipped topping and remaining root beer.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Frost cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: onion-beef macaroni casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat well on all sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in onion soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water. Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Mix together the ground beef, spices, chilies and mushroom soup.
Spray bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Take shells and cover bottom of dish.
Spread sausa over shells.
Pour meat mixture onto shells and spread out. Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Continue to layer:
shells, sausa, meat and cheese.
Pour milk over top (this keeps casserole from being dry).
On top layer put dab of sour cream (optional).
Bake at 350° for around 25 to 30 minutes.
When cheese turns brown, take out of oven.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and let cool.
Add egg.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water until dissolved. Add egg; mix.
Gradually add flour, blending well.
Place in a large covered container in refrigerator overnight.
Use dough as you need to.
It will keep several days in refrigerator.
When ready to use, roll out dough on a floured waxed paper, small amount at a time.
Cut with biscuit cutter; brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine and mix well.
Spoon out small amounts of mixture in hot cooking oil.
Let brown.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: *How much you use depends on how much you like blueberries.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, eggs and margarine.
Stir in onions, cheese, cottage cheese and broccoli.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Press as much liquid from spinach as possible.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper, garlic powder and sesame seed.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in 350° gas oven 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken devine
directions: Boil chicken in salted water for 45 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Crumble crackers and spread over chicken.
Spread sliced mushrooms next.

title: cinnamon apple rolls
directions: Combine flour, 2 tablespoons of sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk and 1/2 cup Crisco oil.
Stir just enough to hold dough together.
Place on lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 strokes.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick rectangle.
Cover dough with combined apples, 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 1-inch thick pieces.
Combine 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup Crisco oil and nuts in bottom of a
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, until desired brownness.
Immediately turn upside-down onto large platter or cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes about 8 rolls.

title: deep fried chicken tenders
directions: Mix milk, egg, pepper, salt and paprika together.
Add chicken tenders and let set for 1 hour.
Take out and drain well.
Roll in flour.
Drop into hot oil and cook for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: mini shrimp quiche
directions: Separate biscuits into 24 halves; press into greased mini muffin cups.
Place 2 shrimp in each cup.
Mix remaining ingredients except Swiss cheese.
Add 2 tablespoons of mixture to each cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: dutch apple pudding(heart healthy - fat-free)
directions: Pour warm milk in bowl, stir in sugar or substitute, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour this over bread crumbs and let soak.

title: cream of broccoli and mushroom soup
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces and steam in small amount of water (do not overcook).
Saute mushrooms and chopped onion together in butter (do not brown).
Add the flour as if to make gravy, then add chicken broth and cook until thickens.
Add broccoli and slowly add half and half.
Let simmer a short time to blend.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and shake to coat well.
In large skillet, melt butter with lemon juice over medium heat.
Brown chicken on both sides. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until tender, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: apple graham dessert
directions: Place one graham cracker on serving plate.
Spread with 2 heaping tablespoons of applesauce.
Repeat layers, ending with applesauce.
Spread with whipped topping over top and sides. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before slicing.
Serves 2.

title: country pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Roll pastry on lightly floured surface to form 13 inch circle. Fit into 9 inch pie plate. Trim edges; flute. Set aside.

title: cracker desserts
directions: Crush crackers; moisten with oleo.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cracker mixture.
Save 1/2 cup.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream.
Pour over cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well and add Cool Whip and strawberries.
Put in graham cracker pie crust and chill.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower as directed.
Heat soup and cheese until cheese melts and add broccoli and cauliflower which have been drained well.
Add diced onion.
Pour into casserole dish and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Put bread into the toaster. When done, take it out and butter bread.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Other fruits may be added or substituted.

title: fruit squares
directions: Sift together flour, powdered sugar, baking powder and salt. Add shortening and work as for pie dough.
Beat eggs, add milk and vanilla.
Add liquid to first mixture, mix well and work until it works away from your hands (you can add the rest of the milk at this time if needed).
Divide into 2 parts.
You may chill dough for a short time for easier handling.
Roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Add any filling.
Make slits across top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Slowly pour milk into lemon juice and whip until thick.
Add Cool Whip and whip until thick and lumps are gone.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until ready to serve. Great summer treat!

title: quick candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook yams, brown sugar and butter in microwave dish until hot. Put marshmallows to taste on top and place under broiler until toasty brown.

title: cauliflower potato salad(low carb)
directions: Microwave cauliflower with onion for 3 to 5 minutes (until heated through). Drain and cool. Chop cauliflower. Add chopped eggs and other ingredients. Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: country quickie corn pudding souffle
directions: Melt butter in 6-inch deep casserole.
Beat the rest of the ingredients together and pour into casserole.
Add some pepper. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring to a boil
pineapple and sugar.
Take off and add cherry Jell-O and cold
water;
set
aside
to cool.
Whip Pet milk and add cream
cheese
and
whip,
then add nuts and pour into Jell-O mixture.
Top
with Dream Whip or whipped topping. Refrigerate.

title: cinnamon hazelnut biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet or line with parchment paper.
In a medium bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder and salt; mix into the egg mixture.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Put in microwave-safe large bowl and cook 6 minutes.
Stir. Cook another 4 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into prebaked crust or graham cracker crust and store in refrigerator.

title: roast wild duck
directions: Brush the duck generously with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Place the orange and onions in the cavity.
Roast in a covered roasting pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove cover last 15 to 20 minutes to allow skin to brown.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef and drain.
Put in small crock-pot.
Add drained tomatoes and cheese.
(Keep liquid from tomatoes; you may need to add some liquid.)
Keep hot.
Serve with Fritos.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain until barely moist.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and soup mix.
Add spinach and water chestnuts.
Mix well and let stand several hours.

title: smoked chicken
directions: Salt, pepper and dry chicken.
Put on liquid
smoke, lemon pepper marinade and dot with butter.
Place skin side up.
Begin baking at 400°, then turn down to 350° and baste with smoke as it cooks.

title: speedy beer bread
directions: Combine well.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Mix with already prepared boxed mix and several tablespoons of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: swedish pancake
directions: Mix first four ingredients until batter is lumpy.
Melt margarine and add to batter.
Bake in buttered baking dish at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake another 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve hot, covered with fruit and whipped cream.
For baking dish, a pie plate works well or two smaller dishes.

title: chocolate loaf cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar and peanut butter in bowl. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in small saucepan or double boiler.
Remove dough from refrigerator and roll into small balls.
Insert toothpick in center and dip in chocolate sauce.
Place on wax paper.

title: maltex date bread
directions: Pour water over cereal and dates; let stand 20 minutes.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix meat, sauce, salt and pepper; simmer for 20 minutes. In a small bowl, combine sour cream, green onions and cream cheese; set aside. Spray a 2-quart casserole dish with cooking spray; add pasta. Spread the sour cream mixture over the pasta. Add meat mixture next and sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake for 25 minutes. Uncover and bake
for an additional 5 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream(french)
directions: Thoroughly combine milk, egg yolks, salt and sugar.
Cook slowly in double boiler or heavy saucepan until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Cool.
Add vanilla and half and half.
Pour into freezer cream can.
Freeze.
(Makes 1 1/2 quarts.)

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in pie pan. Spread over crackers!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy, add oil and sugar, mix well by hand.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to batter.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine buttermilk and soda and let stand a few minutes.
Cream sugar and oleo; add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flour alternately to creamed mixture; stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into batter gently.
Stir in nuts and coconut very gently.
Spread into 3 layers and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done (or bake in Bundt pan for about 50 minutes at 325°).
Frost cooled cake with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: elk mincemeat
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Seal in glass jars.
Makes 10 quarts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl; mix well.
Stir in apples and pecans (batter will be very stiff).
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Fix cake mix according to box adding 1 package of dry instant pudding.
Mix pineapple and juice with sugar.
Punch holes in cake after baking and pour pineapple mixture over it.
Let cool.
Fix remaining box of pudding according to package directions.
Spread over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Top with coconut. Keep refrigerated.
Best when set overnight.

title: three soup chicken
directions: Mix rice and soups together.
Melt oleo in pan and pour soup mixture into pan.
Place chicken parts of large fryer, skin side up, on the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: crunchy chicken nibblers
directions: Dip chicken into 3/4 c. dressing.
Coat with stuffing.
Place chicken on baking sheet.
Bake at 400 for 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
In small saucepan mix remaining dressing and orange juice over medium heat.
When warm serve with chicken for dipping.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Make cake as directed, then add dry pudding and can of cherry pie filling.
Cook until done.
Cool completely.
Frost; garnish with sprinkles and cherries.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Use enough milk to make a sticky dough.
Flatten into 6 to 8 patties.
Brown in oil in skillet over medium heat.
Turn once.
Brown other side, cooking about 8 minutes altogether.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix the peanut butter, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Roll into balls and refrigerate.
Melt in a double boiler the chocolate chips and candy wax.
Put toothpicks in balls; dip 3/4 of the way.

title: halbert's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Put in baking dish and bake with tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cocoa-nut balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla together until fluffy.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together; add to creamed mixture, blending thoroughly.
Add pecans; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes; do not brown. Cool, then roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole a child can make
directions: Mix milk, chow mein noodles, soups and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 8 egg pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, start with flour and end with flour.
Add flavoring and bake approximately 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Do not preheat oven; start in cold oven.
Cook in a deep tube pan.
It makes a big cake.

title: fat free refried beans
directions: Drain beans.
Cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer until very tender, stirring occasionally and adding water if needed.
It should be thick and soupy.
Add salt to taste. Blend with hand blender until fairly smooth, still with some whole beans.
Cook to thicken if necessary.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs. Blend. Add food color, water and cocoa. Blend in buttermilk. Add flour and salt gradually. Add vanilla. Beat until mixed well. Mix vinegar and soda together in separate bowl. Add to batter. Stir. (Do not beat the vinegar/soda mixture in with a mixer.) Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: seafood salad delight
directions: Cook pasta, drain and chill.
Dice or shred crab.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery, onions and chilled pasta.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: fudgsicles(day care treats)
directions: Mix all together and pour into Tupperware Ice Tups or paper cups and freeze.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine sugar, spices (salt and pepper) and mustard.
Mix well.
Combine other ingredients and cook on low heat for about an hour.
Keep well stirred.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: pulled molasses candy
directions: Cook all ingredients together until brittle when tried in cold water.
Remove from range and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Do not stir, but turn at once onto a large greased pan.
As soon as cool enough to handle, pull without squeezing.
Cut in small pieces.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon and place on paper towel.
Brown onions and peppers in drippings.
Add tomatoes, sauce and bacon to the rice.
Pour in greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until rice is dry enough to separate.
May add 1 pound cooked shrimp, 1 cup cooked sausage, pork or ham.

title: hamburg supreme
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Meanwhile, combine cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream in bowl.
Brown hamburg in skillet with onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Add tomato sauce and mix.
In large casserole (at least 5-inches deep), arrange in 3 layers, noodles, cheese and sour cream mixture and hamburg mixture.
Do not stir layers together.
Sprinkle grated cheese and parsley on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Leave in oven at 200° until ready to serve.

title: yum dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13 cake pan, put a layer of crushed pineapple with the juice.
Then add pie filling on top of pineapple.
Then add box of dry cake mix over the top.
Take thin slices of butter or margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake for 48 to 54 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Very good dip for raw vegetables.

title: lisa's fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients (except fruit) together; put in a bowl.
Cut up fruit, such as apples, oranges and strawberries; place on platter around bowl.
Serve.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together; will keep for a good while.

title: appetizer hots
directions: Cut wieners into bite-size pieces, about 1 inch in length. Combine enchilada sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan.
Add wieners to sauce.
Heat to boiling and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.
Place in a fondue pot and keep warm.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes about 36 appetizers.

title: pumpkin-pecan pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
cinnamon and salt.
Stir in pumpkin, eggs, corn syrup and vanilla.
Turn into the pie shell and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake
at
for 40 minutes.
Serve with Spicy Whipped Cream.

title: easy raisin cake
directions: Boil the raisins, sugar, shortening and 1 cup water for 3 minutes; let cool.
Add the flour, soda, salt and spices.
Bake in very slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until pulls from sides of pan, in a 9-inch square greased pan.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast beef on rack in open roasting pan at 350° for about 40 minutes per pound. Cool and slice.

title: fried chicken
directions: Select young chickens.
Disjoint and cut up as for fricassee. Season with salt and pepper, roll each piece in flour.
Cook in covered skillet slowly in fat for 20 minutes.
Place skillet in oven at 400° and cook 10 minutes uncovered; then add boiling water.
Cover and leave in oven another 15 minutes.
Heat may be turned off on oven during last 10 minutes of cooking.
Large covered roaster may be used instead of skillet where several chickens are cooking at one time.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and beat at high speed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours for firmness.
Add remaining Cool Whip to top of pies.

title: potato-ground beef bake
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add green pepper, soup, salt and pepper; set aside.
Layer potatoes and onion in greased casserole.
Spoon ground beef mixture over layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: "company's coming" pie
directions: Beat whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff; add sugar and gradually fold in soda crackers (rolled fine). Add nuts and vanilla; place in lightly greased pie pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Score fat on chops and brush both sides with Worcestershire sauce.
Arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish so "tails" are in center.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back 1 corner to vent. Microwave on High for 14 minutes, turning after 7 minutes.
Drain off liquid.
In small bowl, combine soup, water, salt and pepper. Spread over chops.
Top with onion.
Insert temperature probe so tip is in liquid on bottom of dish.
Cover tightly with plastic, arranging loosely around probe to vent.
Microwave at Auto Simmer for 4 to 5 hours.

title: easy bread
directions: Using wire whisk, dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in oil, salt and sugar until dissolved.
Using wooden spoon, stir in 5 1/2 cups flour.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining flour over dough and knead until easily handled.
Divide into 2 parts and put into 2 greased loaf pans.
Place pans in warm area and cover with towel or cloth napkin.
Let rise to double its size.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: fish souffle
directions: Add onion juice, salt and pepper with white sauce.
Stir in beaten egg yolks and add flaked fish.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 60 minutes. Serve from same dish.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix crackers, nuts and 1/2 of the sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla and remaining sugar.
Fold into cracker and nut mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Chill and top with whipped cream. This is excellent.

title: fudgy mocha nut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, water, eggs, instant coffee and chocolate chips. Whisk until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Bake in roaster in a 300° oven for 5 1/2 to 6 hours (until fairly thick, gets thicker as it cools).
Spoon into jars while still warm.

title: strawberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Mix the rhubarb and sugar together until it's juicy.
Bring to a boil and boil 12 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 large package strawberry Jell-O.
Bottle in canning jars.
Process in boiling water for 5 minutes.

title: no work fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt chocolate pieces.
Stir in condensed milk, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or until firm. Cut in pieces.

title: 6 bean salad
directions: Mix all except barbecue sauce.
Stir to blend.
Pour barbecue sauce over beans and do not stir.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Beginning with lettuce, layer ingredients in order given. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: lemon sauce for homestyle bread pudding
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove sauce from heat; stir in butter, lemon rind, juice and salt.
Makes 9 servings.

title: super fudgy chocolate cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips and margarine with condensed milk.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Divide dough into thirds; shape each into 8-inch roll. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices; place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until tops are slightly crusted. Cool 2 to 3 minutes before removing from baking sheets.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger, salt, pepper and onion.
Stir in season mix from scalloped potatoes.
Mix well.
Add potatoes, frozen vegetables and tomatoes, stir.
Add 3 cups water.
Simmer until potatoes are done and desired thickness is reached.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Cook
frozen
vegetables.
Saute
onion and celery in a little oleo.
Mix
all
ingredients except crackers and oleo. Place in casserole dish.
Melt oleo and mix with crackers and break over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a large bowl, combine oatmeal, whole wheat flour, sugar, salt and margarine.
Pour boiling water over all and mix well; when lukewarm, stir in yeast. Stir in approximately half of flour; turn out on floured surface and knead in rest of flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double in size; punch down.
Shape into 2 loaves; place in greased bread pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Brush tops with margarine.

title: blueberry kuchen(koo shon)
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and egg.
Knead and roll out to approximately 12 x 15 x 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Spread blueberries and roll up like jelly roll.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil, except leave top slightly opened for steam to escape.
Place in pan with 1-inch water and steam on top of stove for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(Make sure the water doesn't boil away.)
Top with sauce and serve hot.

title: company punch
directions: Combine punch and undiluted limeade and orange juice concentrates.
Slowly stir in chilled soda and ale.
Add ice. Float citrus slices on top.
Makes 20 (6-ounce) servings.

title: squash croquettes
directions: May chop squash and onion in food processor.

title: oat bread
directions: Soak oats in boiling water; let rest 20 minutes. Mix yeast in 1/3 cup lukewarm water. To the oatmeal mixture, add salt, molasses or honey, oleo and yeast mixture. Add flour, 2 cups at a time, kneading in the last 2 cups. Shape mound and let rise in a greased bowl for 2 hours or more. Cut down with a knife several times. Shape in 2 greased loaf pans. Let rise. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: In a skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, eggs and cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour over bottom mixture.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Score top while hot but do not try and remove until cool. Scoring top while hot prevents further cracking and crumbling when finally removed from pan.
Be sure and "do not" overbake.
Watch your time.

title: apple goodie
directions: Grease a 7 x 11-inch dish.
Place apples in dish.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Cover apples with mixture. Combine margarine, oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, soda and baking powder until crumbly.
Place on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ground beef and potato pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add bread crumbs.
Spread meat mixture on bottom of pan.
Spread corn over meat mixture.
Spread potatoes over corn and meat.
Dribble melted margarine and gravy.
Bake at 425° until brown (20 to 25 minutes).

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out or spoon into buttered roll pan or baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease bottom of 2 loaf pans. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
