title: canned green beans
directions: Boil water.
Put beans into pan with all other ingredients. Pour boiling water over beans and boil for 30 minutes.
Take beans out and put into jars.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
In a second pan, melt cheese and stir in milk.
Add salsa to cheese and stir.
Then stir in ground beef. Let it simmer 4 minutes.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: rolls or pizza crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; combine with milk and melted margarine.
Add to dry ingredients.
Let rise in warm place 1 to 2 hours.
Spread onto oiled pizza pan.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Add pizza sauce and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Beat in peanut butter and powdered sugar. Slowly beat in milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Put in crust. Refrigerate (also freezes well).
Very good served with hot fudge and peanuts sprinkled on top.

title: hog's head cheese(souse)
directions: Have butcher clean hog's head.
Boil the head in water to cover until meat falls off bones.
Mince the hog's head meat (fine), removing all small bones.
Take water the head was boiled in and add to meat until consistency of thin pudding.
Season and pour into molds.
This will harden into a jelly which can be sliced.
Serves 12 or more.

title: southwestern roll-ups
directions: Spread dressing and salsa on each tortilla; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat; roll up.

title: louisiana pork chops
directions: In ovenproof skillet, heat oil; fry chops until lightly browned.
Place 1/2 cup rice on top of each chop.
Sprinkle onion and green pepper on top of rice.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Chop all vegetables and parsley.
Saute first 3 items in oil. Add down to cabbage and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl mix chicken, eggs and celery.
In a second bowl blend mayonnaise, salt, lemon juice, Accent, soup, onion and pimento.
Add to chicken mixture.
Place in a large casserole dish.
In another bowl combine potato chips, grated cheese and almonds.
Sprinkle over the top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato soup
directions: In soup pot, place broth, potatoes, onion and juice, celery and juice, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add instant potato flakes and milk.
Bring back to boil.
If not thick enough, add more potato flakes.

title: heavenly rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and warm water together.
Set to rise. Cook oleo,
milk
and sugar on stove until oleo is melted and sugar dissolved.
After
yeast
has risen and cooked milk has cooled
to lukewarm, add to above mixture the eggs.
Work in a cup at
a time
the flour.
After the flour is mixed in well, put
the dough
in
a
greased, covered dish and leave in the refrigerator until about 2 hours before baking.
Roll out the dough
on
a floured
surface and cut circles.
Fold the roll over
and
pinch it together around the edge.
Place the rolls on
lightly
greased cookie sheets and cover them with a light cloth and
let
them rise from 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about 10 to 12 minutes, depending on the size of the roll.

title: german chocolate cake frosting
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, milk, eggs and shortening.
Cook over medium heat; mix until it comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: no knead hot rolls(janis boyett)
directions: Rinse a large mixing bowl with hot water to warm it.
Measure 3/4 cup warm water into warm bowl.
Stir in 2 packages of yeast until dissolved.
In separate bowl, mix the salt, eggs, 2 cups flour, sugar and melted butter.
Add this mixture to the yeast. Mix well and add 2 more cups flour.
Mix until smooth, scraping bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise until doubled (about 2 hours).
Place dough on floured surface and divide into 2 balls. Pat out into 2 large circles.
Cut each circle in 8 pie shaped pieces.
Roll each piece up, starting with large end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise again until doubled (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Bake at 400° until golden brown (12 to 15 minutes).
Brush with melted butter.

title: finger food
directions: Combine salsa and cream cheese in a bowl.
Mix until "pink." Add diced chiles.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on tortillas, roll them up and place in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Remove; cut ends off roll and slice in 1/2-inch sections and serve.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown meat.
Add everything else.
Put on English muffins or bread.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes.
This is good kept in refrigerator.

title: orange fantasy salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Fold in
Cool Whip.
Garnish with orange slices. Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Leave small amount of tomato soup to pour over meat loaf after you put it in the pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: no crust egg custard pie
directions: Mix 18 seconds.
Pour into greased glass 9-inch pie pan.
Cook at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter and saute mushrooms and onions until soft.
Add flour and make white sauce using broth and cream.
Add seasonings and simmer over hot water in double boiler for 30 minutes.
Stir in grape juice.
Add a bit of hot sauce to beaten egg yolk and fold into hot sauce.
(If sauce does not thicken, add another yolk.
Just before serving, add parsley and seafood and heat through by sprinkling with Parmesan crumbs and baking for 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Sprinkle with more parsley just before serving over rice.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in deep 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla and blend well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Gently stir in baking soda until light and foamy. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool for 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir ingredients together and place in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: lasagne casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Saute ground chuck and garlic salt in heated oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano flakes; simmer 20 minutes.
Drain noodles.

title: fish marinade
directions: Marinate fish in refrigerator for at least four hours.
Grill over charcoal.
Best with larger fish steaks.

title: mulled cider
directions: In square piece of cooking cheesecloth, measure all spices and orange peel.
Tie with string.
Steep the spice bag in cider on low heat for one hour.
Serve hot as is, or add a shot of cider.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fry in small amount of grease (like pancakes).
Very delicious and easy to make.
Even the kids like it!

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and set aside.
Melt 1/2 stick or less of butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour in mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, sprinkle with grated cheese and let melt before serving.

title: forty garlic chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Pour oil over chicken in a heavy 3-quart casserole.
Turn chicken in oil to coat evenly.
Add celery, onions, garlic, herbs, seasoning and cognac.
Mix well.
Cover casserole with foil and then with lid.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Serve, from pot, hot or at room temperature.
As you eat, squeeze cooked garlic onto toasted French bread.
It's surprisingly mild.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix like regular pie crust, only do not use water.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Use fork to crumble the crust and leave in pan.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake 1/4 hour more.

title: sour cream yale cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl, oleo, sugar, egg and sour cream until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Bake at 350°.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in fat with fork or two knives until crumbly.
Add milk.
Mix enough to wet dry ingredients.
Drop dough from a tablespoon on greased baking pan. Bake at 450° (very hot oven) 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: jan's quick trifle
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Add sherry extract.
Let stand while breaking cake into crumbs.
Stir whipped cream through the pudding.
Add cake to mixture and garnish with maraschino cherries (cut up).
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange onion slices over rice.
Combine soup, water and seasonings.
Mix well and pour over rice and onions.
Place chicken pieces on top, evenly spaced, skin side up.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients together.
Ad eggs and remaining ingredients one at a time.
Stir well after each addition.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water. Melt margarine. Mix with sugar in huge bowl. Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast. Stir in flour until well mixed. Place in airtight container and keep in refrigerator.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs, evaporated milk and cream-style corn.
Pour into ungreased baking dish.
Add sliced margarine on top. Bake at 350° about 1 hour, until knife stuck in center comes out clean.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place water, pickling spice and chopped onion in a 3-quart pot. Bring to a boil, then add lemon.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to your taste.
Add margarine and Open Pit barbecue sauce.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Fry bacon and sausage.
Drain off excess drippings.
Add green peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Cook about three minutes.
Add rice and water.
Cover and cook slowly about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add flour, then egg yolk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Put on buttered cookie sheet and pat down until about 1/4-inch thick.
Put the unbeaten egg white on top; spread all over, then press chopped pecans down into all.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Cut in oblong pieces.
Powdered sugar may be sprinkled over sticks (optional).

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in milk, then dry ingredients.
Pour melted margarine over chicken and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May have to raise temperature to brown rapidly.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice (undiluted). Add oranges and pineapple; mix well.
Pour into individual molds or 1 large mold; congeal.
Good with baked ham.

title: sue's beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon flour and salt.
Coat meat with mixture. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add meat and brown quickly. Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove meat and mushrooms from pan.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings.
Blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Add tomato paste and stir in beef broth.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Return meat and mushrooms to skillet.
Stir in sour cream and wine.
Cook slowly until hot.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together in large bowl.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour.
Brown in shortening.
Add onion and saute.
Add other seasoning and water.
Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mom's pickles
directions: Sterilize jar.
Have lid boiling for a few minutes.
Put vinegar, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Get mixture hot.
Place cucumbers in hot mixture to warm.
Pack cucumbers in jar firm.
Put pepper on top.
Pour boiling mixture over cucumbers.
(Cover with boiling mixture.)
Wipe jar top clean.
Put lid on tight.
Process in hot bath for 5 minutes.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash. Add butter and cream cheese.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and next 6 ingredients.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Marinate pork chops in dressing for 6 to 7 hours.
Then take out of dressing and grill.
It takes about 10 to 15 minutes on the grill.
Serve with Stove Top stuffing and green beans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies in a
x
13-inch
pan.
Let cool.
Mix jello chocolate mousse as
directed
on box (except do not use the cookie crumbs).
Layer,
beginning
with
broken brownies, mousse, Cool Whip and Heath bars (crumbled).
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Use a punch bowl or large, clear mixing bowl.
Will serve 10 to 12 guests.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans. Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt baking
chocolate
in
the
top of a double boiler over hot,
not
boiling water; add marshmallows and stir occasionally until
melted.
Remove from heat; with electric mixer beat in butter and milk until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and blend in thoroughly.
Yield:
Fills
and
frosts
two
9-inch layers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in buttered pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle on apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: student ragu
directions: In large frying pan, brown bacon and steak in olive oil.
Add a layer of each vegetable.
Pour in beef broth.
Cover and simmer until done.
Makes its own gravy.

title: chile rellenos
directions: Cut cheese into slices to fit inside of chiles.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks and water slightly.
Add flour and salt. Beat 6 minutes on high speed until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold yolks into whites.
Heat 1/2-inch oil to 375°.
Spoon batter into oil (the length of chili); top with chile (with cheese inside).
As batter sets, cover with more batter. When bottom is brown, turn and brown top side.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Cut
cheese
into
cubes.
Place
cheese
and Ro-Tel in covered
casserole
dish.
Heat for 10 to 12 minutes on Medium power
until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or potato chips.
Also great as a sauce over meats and vegetables.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add strawberries.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix crushed pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Press into bottom of pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Let crust cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Stir into Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
When jello and strawberries are thickened, spread on top of Cool Whip and cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a square baking dish, stir together 1/4 cup of the sugar and cornstarch.
Add pears and cranberries; stir until well combined.
Place in the oven to bake for 20 minutes, stirring midway, or until the fruit is tender and the juices have begun to thicken.

title: peanut chicken on skewers
directions: To prepare the chicken:
Cut the half-breasts into bite-sized chunks.
Mix well in the Peanut Marinade, coating the chicken pieces evenly, and marinate for at least 2 hours.
Stir the chicken 2 or 3 times as it marinates to coat all the pieces.
To prepare the skewers:
Soak 12 wood skewers in water for 15 minutes or so. Thread 5 or 6 chunks of chicken onto each skewer.
Trim 3 inches of green off the tops of the scallions, and slice each in half crosswise.
Skewer the halves on each end of the chicken skewers.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: Cut bread in small pieces.
Add all ingredients and mix well with hands.
Form loaf and place in well greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Once top is done, flip bread over and let bottom bake for 5 minutes.

title: marriage saver
directions: Spread crushed cookies in the bottom of a baking pan or a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread half of the ice cream over the cookie crumbs, then half the topping. Repeat layers and place in freezer.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except rice to soup pot.
Bring mixture to boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until peppers and onions are tender. Add rice.
Heat thoroughly for about five minutes and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion together until both are tender.
Mash with the margarine until very smooth.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and Velveeta cheese.
Simmer for ten minutes, then serve.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk, margarine and syrup. Cook in microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in vanilla. Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken and green beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in greased dish (quart size). Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and put a can of onion rings over and bake another 10 minutes.

title: spicy peach jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Drain peaches and reserve juice, adding enough cold water to equal 1 cup.
Add to dissolved gelatin. Add vinegar and spices and stir well.
Chill until partially set.
Then add peaches and chill until set.

title: polish meat balls
directions: Mix pork, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Wet bread; crumble into meat mixture.
Shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls; roll in bread crumbs and brown well in 2 tablespoons of oil.
When browned, cover with water and simmer 1 hour.
Thicken with flour to make gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes and a tossed salad.

title: old fashion bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight; drain.
Place ham in large pot (4 quart).
Fill halfway with water.
Add beans, cut up tomatoes and juice, diced celery and onions, grated carrot and parsley. Bring to a boil; cover and finish cooking in oven at 300° to 325° for 5 to 6 hours or all day if possible.
Stir occasionally.
Add water if necessary.

title: blackberry cordial
directions: Combine juice with spices and sugar and cook until mixture begins to thicken, about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Add brandy and bottle and cork at once.
Makes just over 4 quarts.

title: barbecue beef grill
directions: Blend cornstarch and hot water in a bowl.
Combine all ingredients, except steak, green onions, garlic and butter. Place steak on a deep platter.
Pour soy sauce mixture over steak. Let stand for 1 hour, turning once.
Saute green onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Cook steak in a slightly greased grill, saving the sauce.
Cook steak to your desire after basting it with sauce.
Remove steak to platter and pour garlic and onion, mixing over it.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 6.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until done.
Slice.
Cook broccoli as per package; arrange in a greased casserole dish. Place cooked chicken slices on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: cheese bowl
directions: First warm the Cheez Whiz and cream cheese in a bowl in microwave.
Next, mix the tuna in.
Cut the middle of the bread out to make a bowl.
Pour the melted cream cheese, tuna and Cheez Whiz in the sourdough bread bowl.
Cut up the scooped out bread into pieces to dunk into the cheese bowl.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onion.
Cut into thick slices.
Separate into rings. Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Pour about 1 inch of vegetable oil in skillet.
Heat to 375°.
Dip onion rings a few times in batter and drop into the oil.
Fry until crisp and brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
If batter is too thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Arrange apples in a shallow 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan. Distribute crumbly mixture over apples.
Sprinkle nuts and water over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Toss first 7 ingredients together and put in greased casserole.
Mix eggs and oil.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco seasoning together well.
Spread in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread sour cream over this mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions and grated cheese. When ready to use, dribble taco sauce over the top and serve with corn chips or taco chips.

title: raspberry thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add vanilla, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend in flour and salt.
Roll into balls and dip into whipped egg white. Roll in nuts.
Place on a cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Press thumb in the center.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and fill print with jelly.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for only 15 minutes.
In top of double boiler over hot water melt together the caramels, milk and butter.
Pour this over baked portion of the cake.
Sprinkle the pecans and chocolate chips over the caramel mixture.
Spread remaining batter over caramel mixture.
Bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.
If desired, you may before returning the cake to the oven, sprinkle 1/2 cup of pecans over the top of the batter.

title: spanish style beef and rice casserole
directions: Cut steak into 1/4-inch wide strips; cut strips into 2-inch pieces.
Heat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat 5 minutes.
Cook and stir beef, bell pepper, onion and garlic 2 to 3 minutes or until beef is no longer pink; place in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to tomatoes to measure 2 cups; add to casserole.
Cover tightly and bake 50 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from oven; stir in peas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add flour and extract.
Mix well.
Bake in greased bundt pan at 300° for one hour.

title: individual party pizzas
directions: Add paprika, garlic powder and catsup to sausage.
Add a little grated American cheese.
Put mixture on rye bread and top with grated white American cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: harold's brisket
directions: Place brisket in shallow pan.
Cover with salt, pepper, 1 package of Lipton onion soup mix and water.
Seal tightly with foil.
Place in 325° oven and roast for 3 to 4 hours.
Parboiled carrots and potatoes may be added last hour of cooking.

title: punch
directions: Mix and add food coloring if desired; chill.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: honey mustard gravy
directions: In saucepan combine ingredients.
Heat through, stirring constantly.
Serve over chicken or cooked vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: poached chicken breasts
directions: Place the chicken breasts in a single layer in a large skillet. Top with the onion, lemon juice, parsley, bay leaf, peppercorns and salt.
Pour over enough chicken broth to cover.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat to medium-low and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until the chicken is just tender and is no longer pink in the center.
Remove from heat and allow the chicken to cool in the liquid.
With a slotted spoon, remove the chicken from the broth and arrange on a platter.
(Strain and reserve stock for another use.)
Coat the chicken with Basil-Lemon Sauce and serve garnished with basil leaves and cherry tomatoes.
Serves 8.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine beans, onion and green pepper. In a separate bowl, combine vinegar, oil and sugar. Pour the vinegar mixture over the bean mixture. Add salt and pepper to taste. Place in the refrigerator. Stir every 4 hours for 1 day. Drain and serve.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle croutons.
Drizzle butter over croutons.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cinnamon fruit biscuit crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip both sides of biscuits in melted margarine, then in sugar mixture.
Make deep thumbprint in center of each biscuit and fill with 1 teaspoon preserves. Bake in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cool.
Makes 10 pastries.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp in 1/2 bottle Zatarain's shrimp boil for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside for 1 hour (leave in boil).
Drain shrimp and add all other ingredients.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve on sliced bread.

title: microwave mexican appetizers
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a casserole dish.
Pour chili on top and finish with cheese.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate all cheese and mix with softened cream cheese.
Add pecans and garlic powder to taste.
Roll into rolls.
Roll in chili powder.
Serve on Ritz or Sociables crackers.
Okay to freeze.
Will make about 5 rolls.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Blend thoroughly.
Roll or cut into biscuits.
Brush on melted butter.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: granny's jelly roll
directions: Beat with mixer.
Cook real thin in a black skillet.
Pour out on a sugared wax paper.
Spread with jelly and roll while hot. Let cool.

title: chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Combine chocolate mixture with flour, baking powder and salt, then stir.
Add vanilla, almond extract and chopped nuts.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hand mixer.
Spread over tortillas and roll up.
Refrigerate or can cut in 1 to 1 1/2 inch slices and serve.
Makes large number of appetizers, approximately 50.

title: flour fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, and water in medium pot. Boil 3 minutes; remove from heat and add margarine, flour, vanilla, and peanut butter. Beat until thick; pour into 8 x 8
greased glass pan.

title: peach and cherry dump cake
directions: Spray bottom of 9X13 pan with non-stick spray.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, alum, salt and pickling spice and pour over cucumbers.
Finish filing jar with water.
Let set for 6 weeks. After 6 weeks, drain and slice cucumbers.
Add sugar; shake to dissolve and let set in refrigerator 1 day.

title: princess pie
directions: Bake and
cool graham cracker crust.
Stir cream cheese until soft.
Beat
in
cup
milk until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and lemon pudding mix; beat with mixer for 1 minute. Pour into crust.
Chill 1 hour or until set.
Top with chilled and well drained fruit cocktail.

title: breaded zucchiniserves 6
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix bread crumbs, seasonings, and cheese in a flat dish.
Dip zucchini pieces in egg whites, then bread crumbs.
Spray a baking sheet with no-stick cooking spray.
Arrange coated zucchini on sheet.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes, turn.
Spray zucchini again and bake 5 to 7 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Stir together well in saucepan both soups, half and half and sherry until mixed.
Cook until boil.
If crab is frozen, press water out of crab in colander.
Reduce heat.
Add crab meat. Heat; do not stir.

title: green salad
directions: Prepare greens in a salad bowl; add celery and toss.
Garnish with onion and avocado.
Add olive oil and lemon juice or other favorite dressing.
Serves two.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° 30-45 minutes.

title: creole burger
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in heavy skillet, stirring to separate meat particles.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 8 or 9-inch square baking dish in oven.
In a saucepan, add sugar, blackberries and lemon juice and heat just to boiling.
Combine muffin mix and milk and stir until blended.
Spoon in baking pan with butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon hot blackberries and juice evenly over batter; do not stir.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft-ball stage. Then add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: crab canapes
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together; add crab meat and seasonings to mixture. Split muffins, then quarter them. Spread crab meat on muffin pieces. Place muffins on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until canapes begin to turn golden. Best when served warm.

title: no rise yeast rolls
directions: Warm milk and sugar just enough to melt sugar.
Take off heat. Check to make sure it is just warm.
Add yeast and stir; add flour and stir in shortening.
Drop by tablespoon into well-greased muffin pan.
Fill about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: iceberg chicken salad
directions: In an 8-cup bowl, mix all ingredients with a wooden spoon and put into refrigerator.
Stir again 2 or 3 times within the first hour.
It's ready; lasts for days.
Makes 8-cup yield.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand overnight (at least 24 hours).
This will keep for weeks.

title: pot roast, italian style
directions: Heat olive oil in large, heavy Dutch oven.
Add meat; brown on all sides.
Add chopped vegetables; saute for 5 minutes.
Thread garlic on wooden pick; add to Dutch oven.
Add bay leaves, basil, oregano, salt, pepper, tomato juice and water.
Cover Dutch oven. Boil; reduce heat so liquid only simmers.
Simmer for 3 hours, or until meat is almost tender when tested with a fork.
Add whole carrots, halved potatoes and celery pieces.
Cook for 30 minutes, or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove meat and vegetables to heated platter; keep warm.
Remove and discard garlic and bay leaves from gravy in Dutch oven.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Beat together sugars and margarine until light and fluffy. Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add flour of choice; mix well.
Stir in candies and nuts.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Top cookies before or after baking with whole M&M's.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: english trifle or "glutton's delight"
directions: Make in a large deep bowl.
Tear up cake in small pieces in bowl.
Dissolve dry jello in thawed strawberries and mix with cake. Slice 1 banana over cake.
Mix pudding according to package directions and pour half in.
Spread on 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Add other sliced banana.
Pour on remaining pudding. Spread on remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on chopped pecans. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix cheese and Bisquick.
Begin adding water, a little at a time, until mix becomes dough stage.
Roll dough out and cut biscuits.
Bake until golden brown.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Mix pre-made gravy, beef, pepper and onion.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine and shake well to blend.
Great on spinach salad.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In large microwave mixing bowl, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Microwave 2 minutes at High power.
Stir; add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into suitable glass dish or pan to firm up.

title: orange slice cookie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Form into 3 small rolls. Wrap in plastic wrap or wax paper.
Let chill in refrigerator. Cut into thin slices and serve. (No baking.)

title: sunshine cake(orville wright's favorite)
directions: Beat the egg yolks until thick (at least 5 minutes).
Beat in gradually the 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in 1 cup sifted cake flour alternately with cold water, vanilla, almond and lemon extract.

title: braunschweiger pate
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine braunschweiger, half of cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk, onion, sugar and chili powder.
Beat until smooth.
Form into igloo shape on cheese tray.
Cover and chill.
Whip remaining cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and hot pepper sauce until smooth.
Spread evenly over braunschweiger igloo.
Chill.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple dessert
directions: Put cake mix, margarine and coconut in bowl and mix like you would for pie crust.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans(yield: 4 servings)
directions: Drain pork and beans.
Place into ovenproof bowl.
Chop onion and apples; add to beans.
Also add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and raisins.
Mix together.
Lay bacon strips on top.
Place in covered grill and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground round, egg and Stove Top stuffing.
Make into balls (ping pong size).
Brown in skillet.
Put in casserole; cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oven in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in bowl until smooth.
Pour over butter.
Add can of fruit with the juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: orange barbecue cocktail wieners
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine barbecue sauce, marmalade and mustard.
Stir in hot dogs; cover.
Microwave at High for 5 to 8 minutes or until hot, stirring every 2 minutes.

title: quick italian asparagus
directions: Place the cooked or canned asparagus in a glass baking dish. Cover with Mozzarella cheese, then sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over that.
Top off with the almonds.
Warm in microwave until cheese is melted, 3 to 4 minutes (sometimes less time).

title: audrey's lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes to blend; stir.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Meanwhile, combine cottage cheese with eggs, seasonings and Parmesan cheese in a bowl.
Place half noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half cottage cheese mixture over.
Add half Mozzarella cheese and half meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° until cooked through.
Garnish with triangles of Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting in squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheesecake, new york style
directions: Blend the cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and the 1/4 cup of melted butter and line the bottom of an 8-inch or 9-inch ungreased spring-form pan. Blend the sour cream, 1/2 cup of sugar, the eggs and vanilla in a food blender for 1 minute.
Add cream cheese. Blend until smooth.
Pour the remaining 2 tablespoons of melted butter through the top of the blender. Pour into spring-form pan. Bake in the lower third of a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
When baking is finished, remove the cake from the oven and turn the oven to broil.
Broil the cheesecake just until the top begins to show attractive spots of brown.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or preferably overnight before cutting and serving.
Cut in small pieces, this is very rich.

title: homemade fudge
directions: In heavy gauge saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, can milk, margarine and salt. Bring to full rolling boil over moderate heat. Stir constantly. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add milk chocolate and semi-sweet morsels. Stir fast until all is melted and smooth. Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Pour into foil-lined 8-inch pan. Let cool and slice up into squares.

title: bourbon or rum balls
directions: Add white corn syrup to bourbon or rum. Mix whiskey and corn syrup with vanilla wafer crumbs, nuts and cocoa. Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar. Keep cool until ready to serve.

title: sweet and sour sauce on chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in
flat pan or baking dish.
Pour bottle Red Russian dressing over chicken.	Sprinkle package of onion soup over dressing.
Next
dribble
jar	of apricot preserves on top. You cover
pan
with
foil and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour
or until chicken is tender.
Halfway through baking you can take foil off.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend Eagle Brand and Cool Whip well, then add the rest of ingredients.
Makes 2 graham cracker crusts.
Sprinkle small amount of sugar on crusts and warm in oven.
Pour pie filling into crusts and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: asparagus bake
directions: Layer drained asparagus, cheese, salt and pepper.
Repeat layer.
Top with bread crumbs and sliced margarine.
Pour 1/2 cup of milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni tuna and corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Butter a baking dish.
Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender but not soft, 10 to 12 minutes, drain. Melt butter or margarine.
Blend in flour and add milk slowly stirring it in as added.
Cook stirring until thickened and smooth.
Add seasonings, tuna and corn.
Stir in one half of the cheese.
Turn into casserole and sprinkle the remainder cheese on top.
Bake at 350 for about 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: melon salad
directions: Whisk first 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Cut desired shapes from melons.
Just an hour before serving, gently fold melon into vinaigrette.
Refrigerate until needed.
Arrange greens on a plate. Place melon on greens and drizzle with additional vinaigrette, if desired.
Sprinkle with ribbon shavings of Parmesan cheese.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and cover foil with whole saltines (40).
Melt margarine, brown sugar and butter together. Boil 3 minutes, then spread over crackers.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over and let stand 5 minutes or until chocolate is melted.
Spread chocolate. Cool in refrigerator and break up or cut into pieces.
Store in cool place.

title: chocolate mousse with coffee liqueur
directions: Prepare pastry shells according to package directions. Meanwhile in a 2-quart saucepan, combine pudding and milk.
Cook according to package directions.
Chill.
Fold whipped cream, liqueur and chocolate pieces into cooled pudding.
Evenly divide among pastry shells.

title: bean mushroom medley
directions: Boil 1-inch of water in a 2-quart saucepan. Add beans and carrots. Heat to boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until almost tender, about 12 minutes. Drain. Cook onions and mushrooms in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in 1-inch of water and butter until almost tender, about 5 minutes; reduce heat. Cover and cook 3 minutes. Stir in beans, carrots, garlic, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 5 minutes. Serves 5 to 6.

title: easy sweet `n' sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with foil for at least 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican spice mix
directions: Combine spices; store in covered shaker bottle.
Use 3 tablespoons of mixture for every cup of dry beans or soup.

title: "walter's award-winning dilly bread"
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat the cottage cheese to lukewarm then put in a bowl and combine sugar, onion, soft butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and dissolved yeast.

title: pie filling-pineapple cream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Toast corn flake crumbs in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine butter and sugar; pour over cereal.
Stir until evenly coated.
Reserve 3 tablespoons for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of baking pan. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
In medium saucepan, stir marshmallows and reserved pineapple liquid over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat in cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth. Fold in pineapple and whipped topping.
Pour half of cheese mixture over base.
Spoon pie filling over top.
Gently spread pie filling to make even.
Freeze 2 hours; refrigerate remaining cheese mixture.
After 2 hours, spread remaining mixture over pie filling.
Sprinkle on reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Makes 16 servings.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Layer a 9 x 12-inch dish:
unwrap tamales, corn chips, grated cheese, chili, picante sauce, sour cream and hot pepper cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lucky chicken
directions: Chop chicken into bite size chunks.
Heat oil in pan.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then flour mixture.
Brown chicken.
Mix wet ingredients and vegetables.
Add to chicken; simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice; garnish with green and red pepper slices.
Serves 4.

title: baked escalloped apples
directions: Mix apples and lemon juice.
Combine sugar, water, cinnamon, margarine and salt and stir lightly.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring once halfway through baking time until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: penuche fudge(in honor of i.t.p.h.a. races, since 1927)
directions: Take the first 3 ingredients and boil until forms a soft ball in cold water when tested.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Stir in chopped pecans or peanuts or walnuts.
A few persons seem to prefer "cashew" nuts (chopped).
Pour the beaten fudge into a lightly buttered dish and cut into squares when cool.

title: cake-like cornbread
directions: Prepare in 2 bowls the cake mix and muffins exactly as directed.
Stir together and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as directed for cake.
Serve with honey butter.

title: tortilla roll ups
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread generously on flour tortillas.
Then, roll and put in fridge for about 1 hour.
Cut rolls into about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick sections.
Serve with hot sauce or salsa if desired.

title: land and sea stew
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Crumble and saute.
Remove fat on paper towel.
In 2 tablespoons of olive oil, saute onion and garlic.
Chop tomatoes coarsely.
Place all ingredients in a saucepan, add sweet basil, fennel seed to taste and 1/2 cup of cooking wine.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add clam juice, heat to a boil. Cook rotelli according to directions.
Add pasta and clams to mixture.
Stir and serve.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and onion. Cool until almost set.
Blend in the sour cream, mayonnaise, cucumber, celery and salt.
Pour into mold; chill until set.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and grated Cheddar cheese together.
Add chopped green onions and garlic.
Spread mixture onto ham slices and roll slices up.
Chill, then cut into bite size slices.
Place toothpicks into slices.

title: cathy's burritos
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Put small amount in center of shells.
Fold edges over.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with salsa and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Serve with sour cream.

title: chocolate chews
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in corn syrup and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, 2 cups sugar and the powdered milk.
(Mixture will be stiff.)
Turn out onto a surface lightly dusted with confectioners sugar.
Knead in remaining sugar.
Knead 3 to 4 minutes until stiff.
Divide into 4 pieces and roll each into an 18-inch rope. Cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Wrap and store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. (I use sugar instead of flour, makes a light crust.)

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and tomatoes in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix together.
When thickens, put in graham cracker pie shell. Refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: french bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk, 1 cup warm water, sugar, oil and salt.
Add flour and mix well.
Cover and let dough rise until doubled (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Fill buns with tuna mixture and replace tops.
Wrap each one individually in aluminum foil. Heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Combine together all dry ingredients except sugar and salt. Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Add egg, molasses and vinegar. Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill about 3 hours.
Roll to 1/8 inch on floured surface.
Cut into shapes.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Cool slightly, then remove from sheet.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, sunflower seeds, raisins, bacon and onion in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Add to broccoli mixture; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Cream until well mixed.
Add oats; mix on low to blend.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Mix at low speed until well blended.
Add raisins and mix well.
Drop onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: pork normandy
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook pork chops about 10 minutes or until brown.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, apple juice, celery and thyme.	Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel candy
directions: Combine sugar, flour and milk.
Heat to boiling point.
While that is heating, pour 3/4 cup sugar in heavy pot.
Heat until it is completely melted.
It will smell burnt.
Add this to first mixture which has reached boiling point.
Cook until soft ball, almost hard.
Take off fire and add oleo.
When cool, beat with spoon.
When color has changed, pour onto buttered pan.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Crush wafers and add to mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Grease and line tube pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 55 minutes.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan (sprayed with Pam) with slightly thawed hash browns; sprinkle onions, salt and pepper over potatoes. Pour 1/2 of the butter over the potatoes; heat the soups, cheese and sour cream and pour over potatoes. Mix the remaining butter with corn flakes and sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Saute mushrooms in hot oil.
Remove and set aside.
Flour meat lightly; brown in hot oil.
Add mushrooms, salt, pepper and wine. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves six.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until desired thickness.
Stir every 20 to 30 minutes while baking.

title: cinnamon raisins biscuits(sugar-free)
directions: Mix cinnamon and NutraSweet in a shaker bottle.
Slice margarine (very thinly) over top of dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and NutraSweet mixture until completely covered.
Roll dough jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place slices in pan. Sprinkle with more cinnamon/NutraSweet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.

title: meatballs
directions: Shape into balls.
Do not bake balls too small.
They will shrimp when cooked.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Drain off grease.
Simmer in gravy for 2 hours.

title: date bread
directions: Cut dates in pieces.
Put in bowl with 1 cup boiling water. Sprinkle soda over.
Let cool, then add sugar, shortening, sugar and egg.
Add date mixture.
Stir in flour and salt.
Fold in nuts. Bake 1 hour in a slow oven, about 325° to 350°.
Makes about 2 small loaves or 1 large loaf.
Can use raisins in place of dates.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 smaller pans.
Mix all ingredients. Beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 9-inch loaf 60 to 70 minutes; 8-inch loaf, 50 to 60 minutes. Cool slightly.
Loosen from sides of pan. Remove from pan and cool completely.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no more than 1 week.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Use teaspoon to make meatballs.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Mix Prego and tomato sauce.
Add meatballs.
Cut up green pepper into sauce with meatballs.
Cook on medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
"Makes great meatball hoagies!"

title: dried beef dip
directions: With mixer, beat cream	cheese.
With wooden spoon, mix in shredded dried beef,
onion, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce. Mix thoroughly.
Shape
into
ball
and
refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Blend squash and onions and cook.
Mix squash and corn bread crumbs together.
Mix oleo, egg, milk and soup together and add to squash and onions.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: oriental marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and use with beef, chicken or fish.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well; store in an airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: jeanne's butterhorns
directions: Place all ingredients, except milk and eggs, in a bowl.
Work together until firm, like cornmeal (at least until butter is worked into flour).

title: caramel puffs
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook butter, brown sugar and corn syrup. Cook for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda to mixture.
This will cause mixture to foam.
Put corn puffs in large roaster pan.
Pour caramel mixture over corn curls and stir until mixed.
Place in 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour on wax paper.
Break apart.

title: spinach balls
directions: Make bite size balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Grease 1-quart casserole with butter.
Mix together cornflakes, lemon rind and cinnamon.
Arrange alternate layers of cornflake mixture and the apples, beginning and ending with the cornflakes.
Combine orange juice with the sugars; pour over the top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 30 minutes or until apples are tender and top is browned.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Saute the garlic, onions and 1/4 cup salad oil very slowly (approximately 10 minutes). Add shrimp to sauteed mixture.
Cook slowly about 7 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool. In a bowl combine the remaining ingredients.
Add shrimp.
Push well down in the liquid. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Serves 4.

title: greek kouloudia
directions: Cream room temperature margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, spices, baking powder and baking soda-milk mixture, mixing well with mixer after each addition.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing after each, until consistency is pliable.
Chill dough.

title: honey dip with fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve as a dip with your favorite fruits prepared in bite size pieces.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add 2 eggs mix until blended. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes until center is almost set.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar gradually and beat until stiff.
Add salt, chocolate chips and nuts.
With spoon, drop by teaspoonful onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Place in 350° oven; leave oven on for 1 minute.
Turn oven off and let cookies remain in oven overnight.

title: hot cheese cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, cornmeal, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese, milk, egg and shortening. Beat with rotary beater about 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve while hot.

title: batter for fried vegetables
directions: Combine cornstarch, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper. Stir in water and egg, slightly beaten.
As you dip the vegetables, stir batter occasionally.
Heat oil to 375°.

title: easy quick dessert
directions: Put dry pudding mix in large bowl.
Add all the rest of ingredients.
Mix or fold together until mixed thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.

title: quick lasagna for 4
directions: Bring noodles to boil and let them simmer until softened. Brown hamburger meat; pour off excess fat and add the spaghetti sauce to the meat.
In an oblong pan, begin layering your ingredients, starting with the meat mixture, next lay 3 pieces of the lasagna side by side.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese on top of the noodles.
Put the remainder of meat on top of the cheese, then noodles and end with the cheese.
If you like to keep a little of the sauce to sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Eat!

title: chicken delight
directions: Make stuffing as directed.
Set aside.
Mix rice, milk, mushroom pieces and soup in a baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts on top and put stuffing on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: homemade hash
directions: Cook all meats until tender and then grind meats, tomatoes and onions.
Mix all this until onions are tender.
Can add more salt and pepper to taste. Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 gallons.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Roll out dough, not quite as thin as pie crust.
Put sausage on top and roll.
Place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours to chill. (For faster results, place in freezer for 1 hour.)
Take out and cut; place on cookie sheet and bake until golden brown.

title: polish sausage with chili sauce
directions: Heat sugar and chili sauce in pan.
Add sausage.
Heat until hot.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Combine water, shortening, sugar and salt in a small saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until shortening melts.
Let cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°).
Dissolve yeast in mixture.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in flour.

title: salad dressing(this dressing is like bob evans')
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, onion and 2 tablespoons of vinegar in blender or mixer.
When well mixed, add oil very slowly, beating constantly.
Add remaining vinegar (never stop blending) and lemon juice and beat until thick.
Stir in celery seed.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: stuffing
directions: Mix all together.
This stuffing is really good with ham steaks.
Can be used with any meat or poultry.

title: my best jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice (1 cup) to boiling.
Pour on jello.
Cool.
Whip cream.
Mix in Philadelphia cream cheese.
Add pineapple to jello.
Add cherries, nuts, cream cheese and whipping cream.
Pour in shallow pan or mold.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Fill half full of sliced raw potatoes and onion.
Add 1/2 pound raw hamburg meat, broken into pieces.
Salt and pepper.
Mix 2 soups and liquid and pour over. Cover and bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all together and put in a baking dish. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: clara mae's mock sweetbreads(serves 8)
directions: Combine meats, crackers and egg mixture in large bowl.
Form meat balls and roll well in flour.
Brown well in oil in skillet (6 or 7 at a time).
Transfer meat to oven baking dish.
Dilute soup slightly with water.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve over prepared rice.
Freezes well.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread.
Dip bread in mixture.
Cook in buttered grill until both sides are golden brown.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Stir Cheddar cheese in butter and melt slowly. Add salt, dry mustard, cayenne and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in slowly the evaporated milk with water. Remove from heat and beat in egg yolk. Serve at once over hot buttered toast.

title: casserole for a crowd
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Mix next 5 ingredients together and pour over beef.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook and drain egg noodles.
Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and green onions.
Assemble in 9 x 13-inch pan: noodles; sour cream mixture; meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy stack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour six (9-inch) round pans.
Blend sugar, molasses and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add salt, soda and spices.
Mix until smooth.
Pour 1 cup batter into each pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 250°.
Let cool.
Stack layers, spreading applesauce generally between layers.
Sift confectioners sugar on top layer.
Can also use apple butter.

title: new york pushcart hot dog onion sauce(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat the vegetable oil over medium heat in a medium-sized skillet.
Add the onion slices and saute for about 7 minutes until golden and limp.
Mix in the ketchup, then add the cinnamon, chili powder, hot pepper sauce and salt.
Pour in the water; stir. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.
Serve over hot dogs.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sour cream.
In a punch bowl, layer cake, pudding and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
(Make several layers for a pretty dessert.)

title: cranberry chicken
directions: In shallow dish, combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge chicken.
In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Brown the chicken on both sides. Remove and keep warm.

In same skillet, add cranberries, water, brown sugar, nutmeg and vinegar, if desired. Cook and stir until cranberries burst, about 5 minutes. Return chicken to skillet. Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally, with the sauce.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: dorothy lynch homestyle dressing
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth. Place in jar and refrigerate. Excellent on lettuce salad or fruit salad.

title: bran muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins.
In a small bowl, combine egg, shortening, sugar, milk and bran.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to liquid mixture.
Just mix until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour over slaw and let set for 1 hour or refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add vegetables and mix well. Combine milk, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add to macaroni mixture.
This will be almost soupy, but as it chills the liquid will be absorbed.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill at least 4 hours (or overnight) before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and salt to boil in pan. Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: butterscotch pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom and long sides with foil.
Heat condensed milk and chips over low heat, stirring until chips melt.
Combine flour, soda, and salt. Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture until dough just comes together.
Reserve 1/2 cup dough.
Press remaining dough into bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of pan.
Pour butterscotch filling onto dough.
Crumble remaining dough on top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake until crust is golden brown, 30-35 minutes.
Cool. Using foil, lift from pan and cut into squares.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Cook sugar and syrup in water until syrup spins a thread.
Add nuts and cook until golden brown.
Syrup will look like it's burning.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir while it is bubbling.
Pour onto greased aluminum foil.
Spread thin.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa in bowl.
In another bowl, cream oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Mix well.
Add to oil-sugar mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon into two greased 9-inch round pans. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Combine milk and remaining sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Spoon evenly on each layer.
Cool and frost.

title: mom's pan fried chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in a plastic bag and shake well.
Put each piece of chicken in bag.
Shake well and cover each piece with flour.
Pour oil in frying pan; heat.
Place chicken in pan. Fry on stove top at medium heat until chicken is golden brown.

title: no bake alpine cake
directions: Mix warm water and marshmallows and let stand for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a roll about 2 1/2-inches round.
Roll in additional crushed graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
To serve, slice and top with whipped cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage stand until room temperature.
Grate cheese and mix with sausage.
Mix Bisquick with cheese and sausage.
Drop from spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add the rest and mix well. Pour into Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased pan.
Dough will be "pulley."
Bake at 400° until done.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into meatballs.
Brown in oven at 350°.
Use with your favorite sauce (Ragu or Prego).

title: curried seafood salad
directions: Cook shrimp in lightly salted boiling water until pink; drain and cool.
Carefully remove the shell from each shrimp; devein shrimp.
In blender, combine vinegar, honey and curry powder; cover and blend 5 seconds.
Through the opening in the lid of blender, on slow speed, gradually add oil into a thin stream. (When necessary, stop blender and scrape sides.)
Cover and chill dressing.

title: fat burning soup
directions: Place carrots, onions, tomatoes, cabbage, green beans, peppers, and celery in a large pot. Add onion soup mix, tomato juice, beef broth, and enough water to cover vegetables. Simmer until vegetables are tender. May be stored in the refrigerator for several days.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together in bowl flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In separate bowl, combine carrots, pineapple and black walnuts.
Add to flour mixture sugar, cooking oil and eggs. Fold in carrot mixture and bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes in tube pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Boil squash in water until tender.
Mix squash together with butter.
Add onions.
Add stuffing mix and cheese, saving a little for the top. Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: best butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and gradually add the powdered sugar.

Mix until light and fluffy. Add the egg and vanilla. Stir until combined. Sift flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar and gradually add to the creamed mixture. Roll out on a lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes and bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Decorate when completely cool.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vanilla, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Then add apples and pecans. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 large juice cans.
Pour equal amount of batter in each can.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground round.
Add chopped green pepper; stir.
Add chopped onion; stir.
Cover until softened, 5 minutes.
Add sauce and paste.
Add water until desired thickness.
Add garlic, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over pasta. Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Saute onions and oleo.
Mix rest of ingredients and bring to boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Boil ribs until tender and marinate with half the sauce for several hours or overnight.
Bake 30 minutes. Remove and turn ribs over.
Add remaining sauce to ribs and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: seven-layer mexican appetizer
directions: In a large glass salad bowl, spread the 2 cans of bean dip. Top this with the avocados which have been dipped in lemon juice. Sprinkle this with black pepper.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on top of avocados.
Chop the large bunch of onions, including the tops.
Layer over sour cream mixture.
Chop the tomatoes and layer over the onions.
Top them with the ripe olives which have been chopped.
Cover with the Cheddar cheese.
Chill!
Serve with the Doritos.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain. Add flour and butter. Lower heat.
Add soups and simmer over low heat about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with sherry.
Stir in.
Add garlic salt and mushrooms.
Add sour cream and stir in until heated (do not boil).
Serve immediately over parslied, buttered noodles.

title: baked ziti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have a
2-quart casserole dish ready.
Mix ziti, 1 cup marinara sauce, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, the Ricotta and Parmesan in the casserole.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini al dente.
In glass or crystal serving dish, mix rotini, sliced olives, broccoli and carrots.
Add dressing and mix gently (not necessary to use all dressing).
Refrigerate for several hours (overnight is okay).
When ready to serve, break bacon into bits; add cheese and mix lightly.
Top with croutons.

title: graham crackers
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Add brown sugar and heat until thick and bubbly.
Pour over cookie sheet, lined with graham crackers evenly fit in one layer.
Pour chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until chocolate chips are melted.
Cool completely, then break apart.

title: how to make dried flowers
directions: To form perfect everlasting, cut roses at their peak.
Set in a tray filled with one inch of kitty litter.
Cover roses with more kitty litter.
Allow to dry in a dark, dry spot for 2 to 7 days.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix vanilla, pudding mix and milk until mixture thickens, then add all of Cool Whip.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer graham crackers, then add 1/2 of pudding mix and then second layer of graham crackers.
Cover with aluminum foil and chill in refrigerator for about 2 hours, then add chocolate icing mixture to top.
Return to refrigerator.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls about 1-inch.
Save 3/4 cup sugar to roll balls of dough in.
Bake at 375°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix ground beef and catsup, press into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes and drain.
Top with potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 3 minutes to melt the cheese.

title: quick and easy chicken dijon in pastry shells
directions: Prepare pastry shells according to package directions. Meanwhile, in skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook half of the chicken until browned, stirring often. Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and mustard.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Spoon over pastry shells.
Serves 6.

title: scallops scampi style
directions: Melt butter in a large baking pan to hold single layer of scallops.
Stir in oil, garlic, wine, lemon juice, Worcestershire, Tabasco and salt.
Mix well.
Add scallops and toss gently. Marinate 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator.

title: tubetini salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions and cool.
Cut up seafood into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients except ketchup; mix well.
Add ketchup until salad looks almost like a Russian dressing (or Thousand Island) color.
Mix again.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nuts thoroughly in a bowl. Mix eggs and oil, then bananas in a small bowl.
Add to dry ingredients; stir well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until firm to touch.
Cool on rack.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.

title: bowl "n" all spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except bread and chill for two hours or overnight.
Hollow out the bread.
Cut the center into small cubes.
Put dip in hollowed bread bowl.
Serve the dip with the bread cubes.
May also add an assortment of raw vegetables to be dipped.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding the 7-Up last.
Chill in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: memphis' special chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Stir until you have a thick creamy mixture.
Add chocolate chips and with a teaspoon, drop onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make sure they are spaced evenly apart, because the mixture will spread while cooking.
Bake in the oven at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: For the first layer, spread evenly in a casserole dish the refried beans.
Second layer, mix together avocados, 1 cup sour cream and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Spread evenly over beans. Third layer, mix together 2 cups sour cream, taco mix, garlic salt and pepper.
Spread evenly over avocado mix.
Next, sprinkle tomatoes, onions, then olives in layers, then a layer of Cheddar cheese, next a layer of Monterey Jack cheese.
Heat to melt cheese.
Use tortilla chips for dipping.

title: ortega huevos rancheros
directions: Heat salsa in saucepan.
In
skillet quickly fry tortillas in oil until soft.
Remove
and
keep warm.
In skillet fry eggs in butter or oleo until white are set, but yolks are soft. Place tortillas on baking sheet and
set
one fried egg on each tortilla.
Spoon salsa over eggs
and
sprinkle
cheese on top. Slide baking sheet under broiler
to
melt cheese until bubbly. Serve immediately on warmed plates.
Serves 4.
Very good.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with veggies or crackers.

title: mincemeat
directions: *Or use 1 cup vinegar and 3 cups water.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Place ham slices on buns. Layer with pineapple and cheese on top. Heat for approximately 10 minutes in a 350° oven. Add bun top and heat for a couple of minutes more. Makes a very different, filling sandwich. May be served with fruit salad or tossed salad for a very easy meal.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, rice, soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion and salt. Mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Toss corn flakes and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix approximately 2 tablespoons cornstarch with some of the pineapple juice to thicken.
It will turn a nice translucent caramel color.
Pour over ham last hour of cooking.

title: butterscotch bubble
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, pudding, sugar, milk and cinnamon until smooth.
Separate each can of biscuits into 10 pieces and cut each biscuit in half.
Put in mixture and coat each piece.
Spread biscuits evenly in a deep dish.
Put chopped nuts on top and bake for 20 minutes.

title: bacon and cheese breakfast pizza
directions: Roll pastry to fit into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese evenly over crust.
In a bowl, beat eggs, sour cream and parsley until smooth.
Pour over pizza.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until pizza is puffy and lightly browned.
Yield: 6 main-dish or 18 appetizer servings.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Precook whole cauliflower in boiling salted water 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Place in an ungreased shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt (optional).
Combine mayonnaise or salad dressing with mustard.
Spread over cauliflower.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and water in saucepan. Stir until mixture begins to boil; cook without stirring until few drops form hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Butter hands and form balls.

title: corn meal corn bread
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, shortening, salt, meal, soda and baking powder and mix well.
Pour into hot greased pan, put in hot oven (450 degrees) for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Combine egg, milk, oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt. Add to liquid and mix.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: quick beefy vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring to crumble.
Drain off drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Freezes well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date nut log
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups of the graham cracker crumbs, marshmallows, dates and walnuts.
Stir in cream; mix thoroughly. Shape into a 14 x 3-inch log.
Roll in remaining graham crumbs. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Slice.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pork and sauerkraut with dumplings
directions: Wrap meat in foil and roast in 425° oven. When done, cut or shred meat into small pieces. Make dumplings by mixing flour, salt and sour cream until dough feels like biscuit batter. Make dumplings about the size of the end of your finger. Drop into boiling water. Cook about 5 minutes. Mix sauerkraut and pork with the butter and a tablespoon of brown sugar. When heated, add dumplings and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into an ungreased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let stand at least 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef and rice creole(method:  one pot)
directions: Dice green pepper and onion; set aside.
Cook hamburger until light brown, stirring continuously to crumble meat into small pieces.
Drain grease from meat into a heat-resistant can. Sprinkle meat with flour.
Add green pepper, onion, salt, pepper, parsley and garlic.
Cook over low heat until onion is tender. Break up tomatoes with a fork.
Stir broken up tomatoes and water into meat mixture; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat; let stand, covered, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: In bowl, mix peanut butter, honey and 1/2 cup dry milk with your hands.
Keep adding rest of dry milk until dough feels soft and playful.
Shape in any form you like or roll it out and cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Eat your creations when finished!

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and corn syrup.
Stir; boil for 3 minutes.
Take off heat; add peanut butter, vanilla, corn flakes and pecans.
Spoon size portions; drop on wax paper to cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Boil until ready to mash.
Drain water and add oleo, salt and pepper.
Mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, onions and bacon bits.
Mix well.
Place slices of Velveeta cheese in bottom of 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Spread potato mixture on top of cheese.
Place 4 to 6 slices of cheese on top of potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until cheese melts.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until completely mixed with electric mixer.
Beat in vanilla, 1/2 cup of flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat in remaining 1 1/2 cups of flour, alternating with buttermilk until smooth. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: buffet beef rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beaten egg, onion salt, seasoned salt and pepper.
Add meat; mix well.
Shape into eight 4-inch square patties, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut cheese slices the same size. Press cheese slice on top each, then 1 bacon or ham slice.
Roll jellyroll fashion; seal seam and ends.
Beat remaining egg with 2 tablespoons water.
Dip rolls into egg, then into crumbs.
In skillet, brown the rolls in hot oil.
Remove to 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Discard oil in skillet.
In same skillet, heat soup and wine, scraping brown bits.
Pour over rolls.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes, baste occasionally.
Can be covered and refrigerated. If chilled, bake about 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo.
Pour over marshmallows and nuts. Sprinkle coconut flakes on wax paper.
Make 3 rolls and roll in coconut.
Wrap in wax paper, then foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight, then freeze.
Take out to slice off some and re-freeze unused candy.

title: hawaiian candy
directions: Combine sugar, cream, butter and ginger.
Boil to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm; add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Spread on oiled surface to harden.
When hard, break into pieces.
Enjoy!

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts; put in bottom of 11 x 14-inch pan.
Mix German chocolate cake according to directions.
Melt cream cheese and butter; stir in powdered sugar.
Pour over cake; do not stir in.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: succotash
directions: Boil butter beans until tender in unsalted water.
Cut raw corn from cob.
Place corn in double boiler with butter, water and milk. Cook steadily for 20 minutes.
Add butter beans, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook together about 5 minutes.
