title: cherry pie
directions: In medium bowl combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Blend thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Place in pie crust.
Top with chilled cherry pie filling before serving.

title: tomato fritters
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients, but do not overmix.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot fat (3/4-inch of fat at 360°) and fry until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Will keep warm in oven for 2 hours.
These are excellent to serve as a side dish or as appetizers.
Enjoy!

title: chicken wild rice casserole(makes 12 servings)
directions: Blend dry onion soup into sour cream and allow to stand for 2 hours.
Place chicken in roasting pan.
Pour sherry and water over it.
Sprinkle with all seasonings and parsley.
Cover roaster tightly.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes or until meat falls off bones.
Remove chicken from roaster, cover loosely and set aside to cool.
Strain pan juices from roaster into saucepan and simmer until reduces to 1 1/2 cups.

title: taco appetizer
directions: Mix first three ingredients until well blended and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, spread mixture on cookie sheet and pour taco sauce over; add onions, tomatoes, cheese and lettuce. Will need the Tostitos to scoop the mixture up.

title: creole haddock
directions: Place fillets in a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over fillets.
Bake at 500° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin stuffed with vegetable pilaf
directions: To cook pumpkin, preheat oven to 375°.
Slice a 4 inch lid off top of pumpkin, angled so it can be replced.
Scoop out seeds and fibers, discard. Cover with foil and replace lid.
Place in baking pan with 1/2 inch water; bake until insides are tender, 50 -60 minutes.
Remove from oven and keep warm.

title: payday candy
directions: Boil Karo syrup and sugar for one minute.
Add peanut butter with nuts and vanilla.
Stir together until smooth.
Put over cereal and mix.
Put on cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered 2-quart casserole dish and add juice. Mix topping; food processor helps.
Crumble it over the apples. Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: hot dog canapes
directions: Cut hot dogs into 8 pieces.
Press biscuits and cut into 1/4. Press in hand.
Put hot dogs into each biscuit and blob with mustard.
Fold and sprinkle with paprika and onion salt.
Spray Pam on cookie sheet.
Bake Ballard biscuits until brown.
Serve; use mustard for dip.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Bring to boil and pour over jello to dissolve.
Add Coke and other ingredients. Chill.

title: ground nut stew
directions: Cook chicken; remove meat from bones and cut in bite size pieces.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in peanut or olive oil.
Add garlic.
Stir in tomatoes, peanut butter, Tabasco, chilies and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add spinach, peanuts and okra, if desired.
Cook 30 minutes.
Stir in chicken and sausage and heat through.

title: sharon's mexican waste basket stew
directions: Saute onions and celery in small amount of oleo. Add soup mix and 4 cups of water.
Cut little smokies in half.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour in large pot. Serve with favorite cheese or or cornbread.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in mixing bowl the cottage cheese, sugar, onion, shortening, salt, soda and dill seed.
Add flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead.
Let rise until light or double in size (30 to 60 minutes).
Knead down.
Make out into 1 large or 2 small loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown.
Brush top with butter and sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook turkey meat and season with garlic salt.
Add soy sauce and water and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook until zucchini is tender.
Eat over steamed white rice.

title: raspberry pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the berries.
Fold them in.
Pour mixture in a glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Check with a toothpick.

title: low country boil
directions: Fill a large pot about 3/4 full of water.
Add potatoes and all spices; bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Add sausage and bring back to boil for 5 minutes.
Add onions and boil 5 minutes. Add corn and boil 5 minutes.
Check all ingredients for doneness, especially potatoes.
Add shrimp and boil until shells begin to separate from the shrimp.
Turn off heat and let stand for a few minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil milk, sugar, cocoa and butter 1 minute.
Have peanut butter, oats and vanilla prepared ahead of time.
Add these last 3 ingredients to the hot mixture.
Stir.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: cream cheese and chocolate cupcakes
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Add chocolate chips.
Set aside.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls, then roll balls into sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or roll dough out and use cookie cutter. Decorate with vanilla frosting.

title: mushroom sauce(served on christmas eve over varenyky-pyrohy)
directions: Rinse dried mushrooms and soak about 5 to 10 minutes in enough water to cover.
Chop mushrooms and put in 1 quart saucepan.
Add cold water to cover, about 2 to 3 inches from the top of the mushrooms.
Cover; bring to a boil, reduce heat to simmer and add fresh chopped mushrooms.
Cook about 1 hour until soft.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla. Add flour, gradually.
Add chopped nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: godfather
directions: Mix ingredients and serve on the rocks.

title: elegant potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream, cheese, onion and 1/2 cup margarine together and add to thawed potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with corn flakes.
Cut remaining 1/4 cup margarine into small bits and sprinkle on top of corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: cherry frozen salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until ice is chopped.
Serve.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in milk and mix the batter until smooth.

title: stromboli
directions: Allow bread dough to rise until double in size.
Press out on greased cookie sheet.
Spread with pizza sauce, then layer meat on top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and oregano on top.
Roll like jelly roll.
Beat an egg and brush on top. Sprinkle with oregano and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add onion, egg and milk; stir.
Drop by teaspoon into hot, deep fat.
Fry a few at a time until brown; drain.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries with sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well.
Cover and refrigerate until jelled.
Keeps well for days! Perfect with turkey, chicken or ham!

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and salad oil together and pour over first mixture.
Mix well and place in tightly covered bowl and chill in refrigerator at least 12 hours.
Will keep for about 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Great accompaniment with meat dishes or dried beans.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Add sour cream and blend at low speed on mixer.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Bake approximately 50 minutes at 350°.
I imagine anything can be substituted for bananas.
I add about 1 1/2 cups of zucchini.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Return meat to gravy and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with noodles and bread crumbs.
Put gravy over noodles.

title: holiday coffee cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
After 15 minutes in the oven at the temperature stated on box, remove and sprinkle on a mixture of the chopped nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Then pour melted butter over all.
Continue baking until done, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm. May be frozen for future enjoyment!

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins and milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Form dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 10 times.
Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on greased baking sheets. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Combine powdered sugar and milk and mix until smooth. Drizzle over warm biscuits.

title: quiche
directions: Mix eggs, cream, salt, mustard and nutmeg.
Saute onions.
Add onions and cheese.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut peeled potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut carrots into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer chicken, potatoes, carrots and onions in a 2-quart baking dish.
Add seasonings as desired.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/4 cup water and pour over contents.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Serves 4.

title: french bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread) together in medium bowl. Hollow out center of bread to form bowl.
Spoon dip into center of bread.
Use center of bread for dipping pieces.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, mayo, sugar and red wine vinegar together to make dressing.
Cut up vegetables to bite size.
Pour dressing over vegetables; mix.
Top with bacon and cheese; serve chilled.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press them to seal.
Put 8 slices of pepperoni in each rectangle. Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up tightly.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, oil, egg yolks and milk.
Gently fold in egg whites and blueberries, if used.
Bake in hot waffle iron for approximately 3 to 5 minutes or until they stop steaming.

title: polish vegetable salad
directions: Cook red potatoes in water.
Meanwhile, boil eggs and in another pot cook carrots, rutabaga and peas until tender.
Mix vegetables together with potatoes that have been peeled and sliced in hunks.
Add pickles, drained navy beans, sliced eggs and onion. Mix mayonnaise, mustard and dill and fold into salad.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with a little paprika, if desired.

title: aunt brenda's chili
directions: In a large pot, brown meat and drain grease.
Sprinkle Chili-O on top and stir in.
Add all other ingredients and cook on medium heat 1/2 hour or more.
Add chili powder as desired.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan the melted butter and crumbs.
Press firmly into pan to form crust.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Press nuts gently with the palms of your hands.
Bake at 350° for 25 to
30 minutes.

title: strawberry pecan salad
directions: In small skillet, melt 3 tablespoons sugar over low heat.
Add pecans; stir until coated.
Cool; break into small pieces and set aside.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine oil, vinegar, parsley, salt, pepper, hot pepper sauce and remaining sugar; shake well.
Just before serving, combine lettuce, strawberries or mandarin oranges, drained, onion and pecans in a large bowl.
Shake dressing; pour over salad and toss.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: el sombrero-calico beans
directions: In casserole, combine pork and beans, green pepper, cucumbers, onion, pimiento, garlic puree, mustard and brown sugar.
Place bacon squares on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: manicotti(low-fat)
directions: Combine cottage cheese, spinach, egg substitute, parsley, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Fill noodles with mixture.
Spray two 9 x 13-inch pans with Pam and line stuffed noodles in the pans.
Top with Prego.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove and cool 10 minutes before serving.
Leftovers can be frozen and reheated later.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta until al dente. Rinse in cold water and drain. Chop the green pepper, onion celery and olives.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan. Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie pan.
Bake for about 1/2 hour.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Mix Coke, ketchup and
Worcestershire
sauce in a large skillet.
Simmer for 5
minutes.
Add chicken breasts; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: southern bread pudding
directions: Mix milk, eggs and vanilla together in a saucepan.
Place over heat until hot, but do not boil.
Line baking dish with biscuit crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Pour mixture over biscuit crumbs.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place baking dish on a pan of hot water in a 350° oven.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: flan
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Blend well all ingredients in a blender.
Pour mixture into baking dish or 4 individual ramekins. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
(If using ramekins, place on baking sheet for easier handling.) Place in preheated oven to bake about 1 hour or until set.
May be served warm, at room temperature or cold.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Boil to soft boil stage the first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Good on ice cream.

title: yellow squash dressing(microwave)
directions: In food processor, process squash until minced.
Add eggs, onion and cracker crumbs to squash and process until well mixed. Set aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar, whole, unbeaten egg, milk and vanilla.
Add other ingredients, mixed and sifted together.
Blend thoroughly.
Let chill 1 hour or more.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large mixing bowl.
Place slices of rye bread on baking sheet.
Drop a tablespoon of mix on each slice of bread.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all but last three ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Stir slivered almonds in melted butter.
Spread over top of mixture.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: different meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pack firmly in loaf pan.
Add 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Grate the cheese.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli scallop
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water.
Gradually add macaroni so that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain in colander.

title: green bean bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Mix in green beans and 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add other ingredients.
Makes 14 molds.

title: chicken dinner-in-a-dish(serves 1)
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Combine crumbs, garlic salt and paprika
on
waxed paper.
Dip chicken in milk; roll in crumbs to coat
evenly.
Arrange
in
one
section of Divided Cover. Place potatoes
at ends of other section.
Add peas to center of section.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on Full power 6 to 7 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir fruits together and mix in Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and serve.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat
oven
Heat butter in saucepan.
Stir in the
salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over the rest of ingredients.
Heat
in oven 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread out to cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into bite size balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Hollow out center of bread; put dip in center of bread to dip.

title: spicy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic in skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir tomatoes, sauce, chilies and
bouillon.
Cook until bouillon is dissolved. Mix flour
and water.
Stir
in
beef
mixture.
Heat to boiling. Cook
1 minute.
Pour
into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick, 2 tablespoons cornmeal and the milk until soft dough forms.
Beat. Drop
by tablespoon onto beef mixture; sprinkle with
remaining cornmeal.
Bake, uncovered, until biscuits are golden brown, 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Saute meat in 1 tablespoon butter until browned.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green onions and green pepper.
Spread half of the noodles in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Add remaining noodles.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over noodles.
Spread meat mixture over all.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Casserole may be prepared early, refrigerated and baked just before serving.

title: spanish brown rice
directions: Brown garlic, rice and onion in olive oil.
Add pepper and brown.
Add chili powder, tomatoes and water.
Bring to a boil and cook on low heat until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 45 minutes.
Check after 25 minutes and add more water if needed.
Serve with grated cheese on the side to be added just before eating.

title: portuguese red bean soup
directions: Boil the ham shanks, sausage and soup bone in enough water to cover.
When meat is almost done, add beans and cook until done. In a frypan, fry onion and parsley until tender. Add to soup stock.
Add potatoes and salt to taste.
Add other vegetables such as cabbage, carrots, etc.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put pie filling on bottom of pan, then pineapple with juice, then cake mix.
Press nuts down into this.
Dot margarine on top or melt and pour over.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fresh blueberries could be cooked and thickened with cornstarch and sugar added.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Mix in flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour batter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate bits.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: ginger pear salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Add ginger ale.
Mash cream cheese with ground ginger; stir in milk.
Add to jello; chill until thick.
Beat with beater.
Fold in 3/4 cup pears and 3/4 cup red grapes.

title: don's holiday treats
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle one jar of dry roasted peanuts into bottom of pan.
In saucepan, melt the margarine.
Add milk, marshmallows and chips; stir until all are melted and heated through.
Pour over peanuts in pan. Sprinkle second jar of peanuts on top.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours until firm, then cut into slices.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 350° oven 30 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
You don't need a crust.
It makes its own.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, coconut and pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 15-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, remove cake from oven and spread Marshmallow Creme on hot cake.
Let cool for several hours before frosting.

title: peach pie
directions: Dip peaches in boiling water and remove skins.
Brush peaches with lemon juice.
Slice about 1/2-inch thick.
Prepare glaze with sugar, water and cornstarch mixture.
Mix well and cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add salt.
Pour hot glaze over sliced peaches and mix gently.
Pour into pie crust that has been first sprinkled with dry bread crumbs.
Cover with top crust that has been pricked with a fork or any design desired.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add beaten egg and vanilla; blend well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk, beating smooth each time to make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured surface to thickness of pie crust, cut in circles the size of bottom of pie pan.
Place rounds of dough on cookie sheet; bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Put together with spicy, well sweetened applesauce while warm.
Let stand for several hours before serving.
Makes 9 layers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in salted water.
Combine milk, soup and pepper. Pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can onions and pimento; bake 5 minutes.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Split and wash green peppers.
Take out seeds; drain.
Mix half and half, flour, eggs, salt and pepper.

title: niemeier's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain.
Add canned tomatoes and sugar and simmer (while you cook macaroni).
Cook macaroni as directed on box; drain and rinse.
Add macaroni to hamburger and tomato mixture.
Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
(Serve as main dish.)

title: chicken almond tarragon
directions: Boil chicken for about 45 minutes or until cooked.
Cool. Tear into bite size pieces.
Add celery, water chestnuts, scallions and tarragon to chicken and combine.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add sliced almonds just before serving.

title: e. g.'s steaks
directions: Use a charcoal grill (electric or gas grill may be used). After grill is ready, sprinkle Tony's creole seasoning on one side of steaks.
Place sprinkled side down on grill.
Now sprinkle other side of steak.
Allow steak to seal about 5 minutes on each side, then cook to desired doneness.

title: baked stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Trim fat from chops.
Cut a 2-inch pocket in each chop.
Sprinkle inside of each pocket with salt and pepper, set aside.
Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and mushrooms; saute until tender. Remove from heat, stir in sage, salt and pepper and bread crumbs. Add enough broth to moisten and hold stuffing together.
Spoon stuffing into pockets.
Secure with kitchen twine or toothpicks. Place chops in baking dish (sprayed with cooking spray).
Add remaining broth.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes or until tender. Serves four.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo
and
water
to 220°.	Add peanuts and cook to 285°.
Add
soda
and
vanilla.	Stir
until
it turns golden brown (just
before it stops foaming).
Pour on a large buttered cookie sheet.
Cool;
turn out on wax paper and break into pieces.

title: sandra's hot dogs
directions: Heat jelly until runny in a crock-pot; then add all other ingredients.
Keep in crock-pot until hot.
Serves well from the pot.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar well. Mix in all other ingredients, then freeze. Take out 30 minutes before serving. This freezes up to 6 months.

title: roasted garlic-potato soup
directions: Wrap each garlic head separately in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour; let cool for 10 minutes.
Separate cloves and squeeze to extract 1/4 cup of garlic pulp discard the skins.

title: merry old sole(for 4 persons as first course)
directions: Butter 4 small baking dishes.
Place a filet in each.
Thinly slice the cheese and put on top of fish.
Top with 2 shrimp each. Pour the hollandaise equally over the four servings.
Sprinkle parsley over tops.
Broil for approximately 10 minutes until fish flakes easily and sauce is lightly browned.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash cooked potatoes well.
Add butter, cream and brown sugar to potatoes; mix well.
Add pecans, raisins, allspice and flavoring; pour into a buttered baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° until souffle is set and marshmallows are browned delicately.

title: deluxe rice pilaf
directions: Soak dates
in
water
for 30 minutes.
Pour off excess and set
aside.
Saute almonds in olive oil until light brown. Remove. Add onion and cook until soft.
Add rice and orzo and saute.
Add water,
juice, bouillon cubes, mint and cinnamon. Bring to
a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in dates and almonds.
Cover and
let
stand 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together, and place in baking pan.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, lemon juice, rind and sugar until creamy. When cool, add 1 pint whipped cream. Let stand and cool.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and dry yeast.
Combine water and salt.
Stir into dry mixture.
Gradually work in flour to make a soft dough that can be handled.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and put in a warm place for 1 hour.
Punch down and shape into rolls.
Brush with oil or melted butter.
Place on a greased sheet or in muffin pans. Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Very soft and moist.

title: crispy cereal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars in large bowl vigorously until well blended.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in cereal and M&M's.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: collards
directions: Clean
collards very well.
After cooking a ham, reserve the juice
or cook 3 ham hocks until tender.
Place cleaned and chopped
greens in juices from meat.
Cook greens until tender, about 1
hours under slow flame.
Add salt, pepper and red pepper.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix in Catalina dressing immediately before serving.

title: ham and cheese breakfast souffle
directions: In buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, place enough slices of bread to cover the bottom.
(I piece them to make sure it's all covered.) Cover the bread with ham and cheese.
Place remaining slices of bread over all, piecing as needed.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard until mustard dissolves.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, cover top with corn flakes and drizzle 1 stick melted margarine over top.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.
Will hold for additional hour at 200°.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: oriental rice
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter in medium saucepan.
Add water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and soy sauce.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, or until all water is absorbed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Beat eggs well and add.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Chop fruits and nuts and mix with small amount of the flour.
Sift remaining flour.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Add flavorings.
Fold in fruits and nuts.
Line tube pan or loaf pans with greased paper. Or spray generously with Pam.
Put into cold oven and bake at 300° until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
This cake can be frozen.

title: cookie cheese cake
directions: Use spring-form pan. Grind 23 cookies. Add melted butter and press for crust.
Press hard.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake box.
When done punch holes all over cake with on ice pick. Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let cake cool.
When cool, put pineapples on top of cake.
Then pour Cool Whip on top of pineapples and sprinkle coconut on top.
Ready to eat.
Serves 10 - 12.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat well again.
Add oil, then flour to baking powder.
Mix cinnamon with apple slices and carefully fold into mixture.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, milk and sugar.
Pour over margarine.
Spread peaches over batter. Sprinkle sugar on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° until crust comes to top and browns.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain spaghetti.
Add dressing, tomato, green pepper and salad seasoning.
Mix all ingredients. Serve chilled.

title: pork tenderloin marinated
directions: Combine soy sauce, honey, garlic, orange zest and pepper flakes in a pie plate. Add the pork tenderloins and turn to coat. Marinate, turning occasionally, for 30 minutes or cover and marinate in the refrigerator for longer. Heat a large skillet over high heat until hot enough to evaporated a drop of water on contact. Lift the pork from the marinade and place in the hot skillet. Cover and cook for 7 minutes, adjusting the heat to maintain steady sizzle or until very well browned, but not charred. Turn and cook, covered, for 7 minutes more. Remove from the skillet. Let rest for 5 minutes before cutting into thin diagonal slices and serving.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine morsels, butter and corn syrup in medium saucepan. Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9-inch pan (nonstick works best).
Chill until firm.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes on High (100%) for 15 to 17 minutes (be sure to prick with fork before cooking) on paper towel.
Let potatoes stand 5 minutes.
Slice off top of potato; scoop out inside to make 6 shells.
(Grapefruit spoon works fine.)
In bowl mash together the scooped out potato, butter, salt and pepper.
Add milk until fluffy.
Spoon into shells.
Add dash of paprika or 1 tablespoon grated cheese on top.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes, turning half turn only.
Reheat in regular oven if desired.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding eggs, cornmeal and cheese last. Bake in 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Makes approximately 18 muffins (grease well) or can be cooked in large iron skillet.

title: five-hour stew
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut meat in pieces about 1 inch square.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven, mixing thoroughly.

title: swiss mushroom chicken
directions: Flatten chicken. Place egg in a shallow bowl. Combine cracker crumbs and salt in another shallow bowl. Dip chicken in egg, then in crumbs. Set aside. In an ovenproof skillet, saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter until tender. Remove and set aside. In the same skillet, melt remaining butter. Add chicken. Cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side. Top each chicken breast with a ham slice, mushrooms and a cheese slice. Broil 4-inches from the heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with beater.

title: reese cups
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and form into patties.
Melt the Hershey bars and wax in top of double boiler. Put 3/4 tablespoon in bottom of cupcake paper. Add patty; top with 1 tablespoon chocolate mix. Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Combine chicken soup, broth and chopped up chicken.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop enough of the stems to measure 1/3 cup.
Cook and stir mushroom stems, onion and green pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bread crumbs, salt, thyme, turmeric and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon margarine until melted in baking dish.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake 15 minutes. Set oven to broil.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: deviled carrots
directions: Saute carrots in butter for 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook 10 minutes longer or until carrots are tender. Serves 6.

title: tortellini seafood salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed on package.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add McCormick salad seasoning to zest up flavor.
Can vary vegetables to your taste.
Try adding green pepper, olives, tomatoes or broccoli.

title: one-step microwave lasagne
directions: Cook beef in a
quart
measuring cup or bowl on High for 5 minutes,
stirring once.
Drain well.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water and salt, blending well.
Arrange 1/3 of sauce in 9 x 13-inch glass
or ceramic baking dish.
Cover with half of noodles.
Spread 1
cup Ricotta over noodles.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella.
Repeat
once
and
top
with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with
Parmesan, if desired.
Cover with double thickness of plastic
wrap.
Cook on Medium (50% power) 30 minutes. Sprinkle with
remaining
Mozzarella and additional Parmesan. Cook on Medium
until
Mozzarella
melts
(about
2 minutes). Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla. Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: chocolate raspberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cake mix, eggs and oil together. Add raspberry chips.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together last 4 ingredients.
Cook potatoes, chop and mix with all the other ingredients.

title: baked new potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine margarine, vegetable oil and salt.
Pour over potatoes and turn to coat.
Bake, uncovered, in a 360° oven for 35 minutes or until tender.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salt water until just tender. Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add clams and the juice.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add milk.
Reheat, adding oleo to round out taste.
Serve.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Scoop out insides of zucchini (melon baller works great), leaving about 1/4-inch sell.
Finely chop zucchini pulp; set aside.
Saute onion in oil in heavy skillet.
Add mushrooms, garlic and remaining reserved chopped zucchini; cook over medium heat until most of moisture evaporates.
Add cream cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well; cook for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and fill zucchini shells.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly and golden brown on top.
Yield:
7 servings.

title: jello
directions: Make jello; put half in refrigerator to jell.
Mix fruit and rest of jello; put in refrigerator to jell.
Put sour cream on top of jello mixture and plain jello on top.

title: deep-dish peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches to measure 6 cups.
In bowl, combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add peaches, almonds and almond extract. Toss to coat thoroughly.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
On lightly floured board, roll out pastry; cut into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Arrange in lattice fashion over filling, moistening ends of strips and sealing to dish.
Bake in 425° oven for 40 minutes or until crust is golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Add enough milk to moisten good.
Mix together and put in skillet.
Cook at 350 degrees for about 35 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel the tomatoes.
Cut them in small pieces and put with all the other ingredients into a saucepan.
Cook very slowly for 3 hours and then bottle and seal.

title: "camp meeting" preacher pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, then egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 4 minutes until golden brown.
Cool pie. Beat egg whites and 5 tablespoons sugar to form meringue.
Pour on pie and brown.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together the margarine, sugar and vanilla, then beat in 3 eggs.
On the side in a separate bowl, mix the flour and baking powder.
Alternate the flour and baking powder mix with the cup of milk into the large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Then add the chocolate mini chips.
Grease 10-inch tube pan and pour mix in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice stuff
directions: Dice onion and saute lightly in large pan or skillet.
Add hamburger and cook over medium heat until no longer pink, crumbling meat as it cooks.
Do not brown, then add 1/2 of the tomato juice; stir in both cans of Veg-All (including juice).
Add herbs and spices packet from rice box, stirring as you add, then add dry rice.
Stir thoroughly and reduce heat.
Cover and let simmer, adding rest of tomato juice as first is absorbed, until juice is used up.
Cook until no longer soupy and rice is done. Serves 4 to 6 people and reheats nicely.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef, ground pork, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until meat is brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with a fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 1 1/2 tablespoons parsley flakes, the sugar, 1 teaspoon of salt and basil.
Simmer uncovered 1 hour until mixture is like good spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: hot biscuits
directions: *If buttermilk is used, add 1/4 teaspoon soda to flour.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Blend cornstarch and water, add soy sauce and heat until slightly thick and clear, set aside.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add carrots and stir-fry for 3 minutes. Add other ingredients and stir-fry two (2) minutes more or until vegetables are crispy-tender.
Add glaze (cornstarch mixture) and stir 1 to 2 minutes until vegetables are well covered.
Cover and cook one minute.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Cut dates fine; mix dates, sugar and butter in
3/4 cup boiling water; let cool.
Then mix all ingredients.
Put in bread pan (loaf).
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and spread in oblong baking dish, forming a crust.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Let cool.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Then slowly beat in 1 quart of sweet milk.
Add dash of nutmeg and fold in 2 cartons of whipped cream.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients, except ice, in blender and blend for 1 minute.
Add ice and blend at highest speed for 2 minutes.
Serve in tall glasses with mint leaf on top.

title: triple fudge treat
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Blend dry cake mix into pudding.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Press lightly into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: hash brown omelet
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Leave drippings in skillet; drain bacon and crumble.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Put into skillet.
Cook over low heat until underside is crisp; add bacon.
Blend eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes. Top with cheese and bacon; cover.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Loosen omelet.
Serve in wedges.
Serves 4.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush Oreos, saving one cookie.
Place cookie crumbs in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour over cookie crumbs. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cream cheese at room temperature. Add eggs and flour, alternating these as you add them.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Place batter in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook elbows in saucepan.
Cook mushroom soup and milk.
When elbows are done, empty into casserole dish.
Moisten with Italian dressing, then add tuna and mushroom soup mix.
Then sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Thoroughly cream sugar with butter.
Add spices and cream. Add egg yolks (beaten until smooth) and vinegar.
Stir in cut raisins.
Add salt to egg whites; beat until stiff.
Slide whites into sugar and raisin mixture.
Cut and fold in thoroughly.
Turn into pastry-lined pan and bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top should be brown and center of filling jelly like when done.
Let cool 2 to 3 hours before cutting.
Serve at room temperature.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt
oleo
in a thick pot;
saute onions, bell pepper, celery and
garlic until tender.
Add soup and 1 cup of water, retained from
boiling
shrimp.
Stir in parsley, onion tops, shrimp and pimentos.
Stir
in rice and half of bread crumbs; cook a
little longer.
Season to taste.
Turn into a 3 quart casserole.
Top with reserved bread crumbs and bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce dessert
directions: Put a layer of graham crackers in a cake pan (9 x 12-inch or larger).
Add cream cheese on top of graham crackers.
Mix applesauce and dry Jell-O.
Put a layer of this mixture on crackers.
Make several layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Fold first 8 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top along with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: old fashion apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry and fill with peeled, thinly sliced apples (pile high in center).
Mix cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Sprinkle evenly over the apples.
Dot with butter; moisten edges of crust with water.
Fit top crust and seal edges.
Make vents or lay top crust in lattice strips over the apples and filling.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: cream of green bean soup
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and brown.
Add onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato juice, potatoes, water and beans which have been cut into inch-long pieces.
Simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Add flour which has been stirred to a smooth paste with milk.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Season and serve.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding as package mix directs. Cool 5 minutes. Add the peppermint extract to the pudding.
Pour into the baked, cooled graham cracker crust. Chill at least 2 hours. Whip the cream that has been sweetened with the sugar.

title: double-coconut cream pie
directions: For filling:
In a medium saucepan, combine the first 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk and cream of coconut. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot milk mixture into the beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly. Return all of the mixture to saucepan.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter until melted.
Stir in the 1 cup coconut and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour filling into baked pastry shell.
